<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 30PT;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#GKOS-20151231X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#2E74B5;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 17.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">
	&#xB7;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;WIDTH:1PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	To further transform glaucoma treatment and care by introducing micro
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#8209;scale injectable therapies&#x2014;including our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	iStent Inject
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	iStent Supra
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	iDose
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	pipeline products&#x2014;that can be performed in minor surgical suites or in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&#8209;office settings with topical anesthetic.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	As of December&nbsp;31, 2015, our research and development team consisted of 66 employees. Our research and development process is supported by multiple clinical research programs and regulatory affairs activities. We
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	currently
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	have 17 prospective clinical trials underway. In addition, our technologies have been discussed in 40 articles published in peer
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;reviewed journals to date.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our research and development expenses were approximately $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	25.0 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, $19.2&nbsp;million and $15.5&nbsp;million in the years ended December&nbsp;31, 2015, 2014 and 2013, respectively. We
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	expect our research and development expenditures to increase as we continue to devote significant resources to clinical trials and regulatory approvals of our new products.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent clinical validation
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	pivotal U.S. clinical trial that served as the basis for the FDA approval of our PMA application by the FDA was the first prospective, randomized, open
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;label, multi
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;center, controlled U.S. IDE clinical trial ever to be conducted in support of a glaucoma device. A total of 29 U.S. investigational sites participated in the trial, which demonstrated that insertion of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in patients undergoing cataract surgery provided clinically and statistically significant improvements in intraocular pressure and an overall safety profile similar to cataract surgery alone.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	To be enrolled in the trial, subjects were required to have mild or moderate open
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;angle glaucoma with visual field or nerve pathology characteristic of glaucoma, a C:D ratio of 0.8 or less, and intraocular pressure &#x2264; 24 mm Hg while taking one to three prescription eye drops. After discontinuation of glaucoma medications, intraocular pressure was required to be between 22 mm Hg and 36 mm Hg. Excluded from the trial were individuals with severe glaucomatous field defects, severely uncontrolled intraocular pressure, angle closure glaucoma, neovascular, uveitic or angle recession glaucoma, prior glaucoma surgery other than iridectomy, prior refractive procedures, known corticosteroid responders, ocular disease that would affect safety, monocular subjects or those with fellow eye best corrected visual acuity, or BCVA, worse than 20/200. In this study, the &#x201C;p&#x201D; values were statistical calculations to determine whether the effects of receiving the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in conjunction with cataract surgery were significant in comparison to cataract surgery alone based on pre
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;specified statistical targets. We specified that any result where p&nbsp;&#x2264;&nbsp;.05 would be significant.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	A total of 240 eyes (239 subjects) were randomized, of which 117 were randomized to receive the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in conjunction with cataract surgery (treatment group) and 123 to cataract surgery only (control group). Of the 117 eyes randomized to the treatment group, 111 underwent insertion of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in conjunction with cataract surgery. Of the 123 eyes randomized to receive cataract surgery only, 117 eyes underwent cataract surgery. At the 12
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;month visit, subject accountability was 97% in the treatment group and 99% in the control group. After the randomized phase of the trial, an additional 50 subjects were enrolled for the safety purposes in the non
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;randomized phase.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Pivotal trial efficacy data
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Of subjects in the treatment group, 68% achieved the primary efficacy endpoint of an intraocular pressure&nbsp;&#x2264;&nbsp;21 mm Hg without prescription eye drops at 12&nbsp;months, compared to 50% for the control group (p&nbsp;=&nbsp;0.004). Of subjects in the treatment group, 64% achieved the secondary efficacy endpoint of intraocular pressure reduction &#x2265; 20% without prescription eye drops at 12&nbsp;months, compared to 47% in the control group (p&nbsp;=&nbsp;0.010). Throughout the postoperative period, prescription eye drops were prescribed in a lower proportion of patients, and initiated later, in the treatment group than in the control group. At 12&nbsp;months, 85% of treatment group subjects were medication free compared to 65% of control group subjects at 12&nbsp;months.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	11
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>

	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage15"></A>

</TABLE>
</DIV>
</EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The overall rate of adverse events was similar between the treatment and control groups and no unanticipated adverse device complications were reported. The trial showed that when inserted in conjunction with cataract surgery for subjects with mild
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;moderate open
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;angle glaucoma, the benefits of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	procedure exceeded its risks.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Additional iStent studies
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Two
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;year results from the pivotal trial showed relatively similar outcomes, although it was not designed nor statistically powered for two
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;year efficacy endpoints. Numerous other studies performed in Western Europe and the United States evaluating the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in combination with cataract surgery have found statistically significant reductions in mean intraocular pressure and medication use. For example, in a prospective, double
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;masked, randomized controlled trial on 36 patients with cataract and primary open
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;angle glaucoma, patients who received a single
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in conjunction with cataract surgery showed an intraocular pressure decline to 14.8 mm Hg from 17.9 mm Hg at 15&nbsp;months. This compared to an intraocular pressure decline to 15.7 mm Hg from 17.3 mm Hg in patients who underwent cataract surgery only. This trial included a washout of medications at 15&nbsp;months in order to remove the confounding effect of glaucoma medications and, at 16&nbsp;months, intraocular pressure was 16.6 mm Hg in the combined group, compared to 19.2 mm Hg in the cataract surgery
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;only group.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Two other Western European studies have demonstrated the sustained efficacy and safety of a single
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	inserted in combination with cataract surgery af
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ter three or more years of post
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	operative follow up. In one international prospective, non
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;comparative, uncontrolled, non
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;randomized, interventional case series study, 19 subjects with mild
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;moderate open
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;angle glaucoma underwent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	implantation in conjunction with cataract surgery. At a mean follow
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;up of 53&nbsp;months, patients&#x2019; mean intraocu
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	l
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ar pressure was 16.3 mm Hg, compared to preoperative medicated intraocular pressure of 19.4 mm Hg. In 42% of patients, no glaucoma medications were used at the end of follow
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;up and the mean number of prescription eye drops used by the patients declined to 0.8 from 1.3 medications preoperatively.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The other Western European study, a prospective, open
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;label, non
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;randomized study, assessed the long
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;term postoperative outcomes of one
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	implanted during cataract surgery in subjects with primary open
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;angle glaucoma, pseudoexfoliation glaucoma, secondary or post
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;traumatic glaucoma or ocular hypertension. There was no preoperative medication washout period and 40% of eyes had undergone previous glaucoma surgeries, primarily laser procedures. In the study, a single
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	was implanted through the same incision used for cataract surgery in a consecutive series of 62 eyes of 43 subjects. In 39 eyes followed through three years, the mean intraocular pressure at three years was 14.9 mm Hg, compared to a mean preoperative intraocular pressure of 23.4 mm Hg, representing a 36% decline. In the same 39 eyes, the mean number of glaucoma medications used three years following surgery declined to 0.3, compared to a mean of 1.9 medications at subjects&#x2019; preoperative visits, representing an 86% reduction. No operative complications occurred during the cataract surgical procedure or during the stent implantation procedure. Over the three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;year follow
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;up period, five secondary surgeries, two postoperative ocular sequelae and two non
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;ocular adverse events were reported.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	12
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<HR ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE='BACKGROUND-COLOR:#000000; BORDER-WIDTH:0; COLOR:#000000; HEIGHT:2PT; LINEHEIGHT:0; WIDTH:100%;'>
</HR>
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage16"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 30PT;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#GKOS-20151231X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#2E74B5;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Additional iStent studies with multiple stents in standalone procedures
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In a prospective, pilot study in Eastern Europe, 39 phakic and pseudophakic subjects with open
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;angle glaucoma and preoperative unmedicated intraocular pressure between 22 mm Hg and 38 mm Hg received two
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStents
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in a standalone procedure. At 36&nbsp;months, subjects not taking medication achieved mean intraocular pressure of 15.2 mm Hg, representing a 37% reduction from unmedicated baseline intraocular pressure. In four subjects who required medication, intraocular pressure ranged from 13 mm Hg to&nbsp;15.7&nbsp;mm Hg at 36&nbsp;months. There were no postoperative adverse events related to stent implantation, except for one incidence of early postoperative hyphema that resolved at one week. The study is designed for follow
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;up through five years.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In another international prospective, randomized study, 119 subjects with open
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;angle glaucoma and preoperative unmedicated intraocular pressure between 22 mm Hg and 38 mm Hg received one, two or three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStents
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in a standalone procedure. In this study, the number of stents was based on randomization and not on each glaucoma patient&#x2019;s specific needs. The study design included a primary efficacy endpoint of &#x2265; 20% intraocular pressure reduction at 12&nbsp;months from baseline unmedicated intraocular pressure without use of prescription eye drops or secondary glaucoma procedures. The secondary efficacy endpoint was intraocular pressure &#x2264;&nbsp;18 mm Hg at 12&nbsp;months without use of prescription eye drops or secondary glaucoma procedures. Approximately 89%, 90% and 92% of the one
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;, two
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209; and three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;stent groups met the primary and secondary endpoints, respectively. In addition, at 18&nbsp;months, mean unmedicated intraocular pressure was 15.9 mm Hg, 14.1 mm Hg and 12.2 mm Hg in the one
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;, two
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209; and three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;stent groups, respectively. No intraoperative ocular adverse events occurred and safety data were similar across all stent groups. By month 18, four eyes had undergone cataract surgery due to progression of cataract. Under the study design, follow
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;up will continue through five years.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	To show the benefits of combining trabecular meshwork stents and suprachoroidal stents to achieve dual physiologic outflow in patients with severe glaucoma, 80 failed trabeculectomy patients received two iStents, one iStent Supra and one prescription eye drop in an international study. In 49 patients followed through 12&nbsp;months, mean intraocular pressure declined 49% to 13.4 mm Hg, compared to a baseline intraocular pressure of 26.4 mm Hg. In addition, 100% of patients met
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	the primary endpoint of &#x2265; 20% reduction in intraocular pressure at 12&nbsp;months.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Sales and Marketing
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In the United States, we sell our products through a direct sales organization that, as of December&nbsp;31, 2015, consisted of 65 sales professionals, including regional
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	business managers, sales directors, clinical relations personnel and reimbursement specialists. Our sales organization is primarily responsible for training ophthalmic surgeons on the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	procedure, helping these physicians integrate the technology into their practices and providing resources to support reimbursement, while also identifying and supporting investigational sites for clinical trials of our pipeline technologies. We continue to recruit experienced sales professionals with extensive sales and/or clinical experience in ophthalmic medical technologies. Our weighted average number of domestic sales representatives increased to 45 for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2015 from 35 for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2014. The higher number of sales representatives in each period helped increase our customer base, leading to growth in unit sales. Increased unit volume was responsible for the majority of the increase in net sales for the three months and year ended December&nbsp;31, 2015.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We invest significant time and expense to provide comprehensive training to our sales professionals so that they are proficient in all aspects of our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	technologies, including features and benefits, procedure techniques and reimbursement. In addition, we provide technical education regarding the eye&#x2019;s anatomy, glaucoma diagnosis, disease states and treatment, and cataract surgery.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Outside the United States, we sell our products primarily through a network of distribution partners located in markets where we see the greatest potential for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	adoption. In late 2013, we formed a wholly
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;owned subsidiary in Germany that employs five direct sales representatives. In early 2015, we formed a wholly
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;owned subsidiary in Japan that employs five direct sales representatives. We intend for this subsidiary to commence a commercial launch in the event we receive regulatory approval to market the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in Japan. Following our initial public offering (IPO), we formed wholly
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;owned subsidiaries in Australia and Canada. In Australia, we have hired a general manager and five direct sales representatives who commenced a commercial launch in January 2016. In Canada, we have hired a general manager and five direct sales representatives who commenced a commercial launch in January 2016. We continually
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	13
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">

	&nbsp;

<A NAME="eolPage17"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 30PT;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#GKOS-20151231X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#2E74B5;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	monitor our international sales progress and will consider conversion to a direct sales approach on a country
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;by
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;country basis, depending on our assessment of market conditions, net sales and profitability trends, reimbursement coding and coverage potential, and other factors. As of December&nbsp;31, 2015, we had agreements with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	approximately 1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	distributor
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	organizations. No single distributor accounted for more than 10% of our total net sales for the years ended December&nbsp;31, 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, 2014 or 201
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our global sales efforts and promotional activities are currently aimed at ophthalmic surgeons and other eye care professionals. Our primary customers include ophthalmic surgeons, hospitals and ambulatory surgery centers (ASCs). We require physicians to complete a mandatory training program before commencing
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	procedures. To facilitate this, we have developed a multi
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;faceted education program that includes interactive webinars, wet
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;lab training, in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;office didactic sessions, observation of surgical cases and off
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;site information seminars. We also offer physician
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;physi
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	cian training that involves pre
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	operative diagnostics
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, procedure assistance and post
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	operative consultations. We believe our education and training programs enable ophthalmic surgeons and other eye care professionals to improve patient outcomes and satisfaction with the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and procedure.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We support our sales organization with marketing programs and initiatives designed to build awareness and appreciation for our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	technologies. These include advertisements and editorial coverage in professional publications, exhibits at major ophthalmic congresses and meetings, MIGS and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	user meetings, and targeted direct
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;consumer
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	marketing efforts.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Reimbursement
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	United States reimbursement
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Reimbursement for iStent procedure
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	There are three key aspects of reimbursement in the United States:
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 17.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">
	&#xB7;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;WIDTH:1PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Coding refers to distinct numeric and alphanumeric billing codes that are used by healthcare providers to report the provision of medical procedures
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	and the use of supplies for specific patients to payors. There are different categories of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Current Procedural Terminology (CPT)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	codes (Category&nbsp;I, II and III)&nbsp;based on the procedure or supply.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 17.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">
	&#xB7;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;WIDTH:1PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Coverage refers to decisions made by individual payors as to whether or not to pay for a specific procedure and related supplies and if so, under what conditions (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	i.e.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, for which specific diagnoses and clinical indications). Payors typically base coverage decisions on reviews of the published medical literature.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 17.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">
	&#xB7;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;WIDTH:1PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Payment refers to the amount paid to providers for specific procedures and supplies. Payment is generally determined for the specific billing code and, in addition, there may be separate numeric codes, under which the billing code is classified, to establish a payment amount.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In 2008, in consultation with and with the approval of the American Academy of Ophthalmology, we applied for and received a temporary Category&nbsp;III CPT code to describe insertion of devices such as the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	using MIGS procedures.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Category&nbsp;III codes expire five years after the date they become effective. Prior to expiration, there are two options: submit an application to convert to a Category&nbsp;I code; or submit an application for a five year extension of Category&nbsp;III status. CPT code 0191T, which describes the insertion of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent Inject
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	devices, first became effective in 2008. Prior to expiration, an application for a five
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	-
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	year extension was approved in 2012
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and expires on December 31, 2018
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. We will need to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	either
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	submit an application to convert CPT code 0191T to a Category&nbsp;I code
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	or apply for another five-year extension by June 2017
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in order for the new code to be effective
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	by
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	January 1, 2019
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We also successfully applied for, and the American Medical Association created, a new CPT code 0253T, which describes the insertion of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent Supra
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	device, in 2011. An application for a five
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	-
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	year extension was approved at the same time as the application for the extension of CPT code 0191T. We will need to either submit an application for a Category&nbsp;I code or apply for another five
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;year extension
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	by June
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2017.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	14
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<HR ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE='BACKGROUND-COLOR:#000000; BORDER-WIDTH:0; COLOR:#000000; HEIGHT:2PT; LINEHEIGHT:0; WIDTH:100%;'>
</HR>
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage18"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 30PT;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#GKOS-20151231X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#2E74B5;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	is approved by the FDA for reduction of intraocular pressure in adult patients with mild
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;moderate open
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;angle glaucoma undergoing cataract surgery who are currently treated with prescription eye drops. Based on data released by
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Centers for Medicare
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&amp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Medicaid Services (CMS)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	regarding total cataract surgery volume in the Medicare Fee for Service program and data published by Market Scope, we estimate that Medicare pays for 70% of all cataract surgeries performed in the United States. Due primarily to strong published clinical data, including the FDA pivotal trial, all MACs had begun covering the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	procedure by February 2013, approximately seven months after FDA approval.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We estimate that 20% of patients who meet the FDA indication for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	insertion are covered by private health insurance companies, and we have secured positive coverage policies for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	insertion with many of these private payors. As of December 31, 2015, we had secured reimbursement for the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	insertion for approximately 80% of individuals covered by private insurance
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	These include United HealthCare, CIGNA, Aetna and all Blue Cross and Blue Shield (BCBS) plans except Anthem BCBS
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Humana and Tricare
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. The positive coverage by most of the BCBS plans is a result of medical policy issued by the BCBS Association (national) in October 2013 stating that
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	insertion is considered medically necessary for mild
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;moderate open
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;angle glaucoma patients undergoing cataract surgery. While BCBS plans, which are independent licensees, are not required to follow BCBS national guidelines, the majority of the plans do so. We continue to work with private insurance providers in an effort to broaden coverage for the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	procedure.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	insertion in the United States is almost always performed in an outpatient setting and virtually all U.S.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	sales are to ASCs and hospital outpatient departments (HOPDs). At the average facility, 70% of claims reporting
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	insertion with cataract surgery will be processed and paid for by Medicare. National payment rates by Medicare to ASCs and HOPDs are determined each year through a complex formula, which takes into account reported costs for each claim submitted. When two procedures are performed in an ASC on the same patient on the same day (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	e.g.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	insertion and cataract surgery), Medicare reduces the payment of the lower
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;paying procedure by 50%. The ASC facility payment for cataract surgery is generally lower than the payment for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	insertion. Therefore, when these two procedures are performed together in an ASC, the payment for cataract surgery is reduced by 50%. We believe that the incremental payment the ASC facility receives for performing
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	insertion in conjunction with cataract surgery over and above what the facility would receive for performing cataract surgery alone covers the cost of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	device and the profit for the facility. The incremental ASC facility payment has remained relatively stable over the past few years, however there is no assurance that this payment will remain stable in the future. If the incremental facility payment were to decrease such that it did not cover the cost of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	device, it could reduce the profit margin of the ASC where the cataract surgery is performed, make it difficult for existing customers to continue using, or new customers to adopt, our products and create additional pricing pressure for us.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Reimbursement for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	insertion and cataract procedures performed in HOPDs was similar to ASCs until CMS implemented a rule change, effective January&nbsp;1, 2016, reflecting a trend by CMS of bundling payment for procedures that are clinically similar and performed at the same time in HOPDs. Procedures covered by these combined reimbursement codes are grouped into levels and reimbursed with a single, all
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;inclusive payment. As a result of this recent rule change, CMS combined the cataract and MIGS/
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	procedure within a single comprehensive reimbursement code, which eliminated the separate 50% facility reimbursement for the cataract portion of the procedure when performed in the HOPD. While this change will result in lower Medicare fee
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;service reimbursement when
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and cataract procedures are performed at the same time in HOPDs, we do not expect it to have a material impact on our 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	utilization rates. We intend to preserve our current HOPD pricing on the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	device. We estimate that approximately 25% of US
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	procedures are currently performed in HOPDs but only a portion of these procedures are reimbursed through traditional Medicare fee
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;service. This change will likely reduce the profit margin of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and cataract procedure for some HOPD customers and could potentially make it more difficult for some existing HOPD customers to continue using, or new HOPD customers to adopt, our products and could create additional pricing pressure on the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	implant.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Physicians are paid separately from the facility for surgical procedures. Unlike the facility payment, for the CPT code that describes
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	insertion, there is no published Medicare payment schedule at the national level, and the physician payment rate is left to the discretion of the individual Medicare contractor. In order to adopt a new procedure, one of the factors that the surgeon evaluates is whether or not payment for the procedure adequately covers the surgeon&#x2019;s time. As with the facility payment, the incremental payment the physician receives for inserting the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	device in conjunction with cataract surgery over and above what he or she would receive for performing cataract surgery alone
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	15
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<HR ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE='BACKGROUND-COLOR:#000000; BORDER-WIDTH:0; COLOR:#000000; HEIGHT:2PT; LINEHEIGHT:0; WIDTH:100%;'>
</HR>
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage19"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 30PT;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#GKOS-20151231X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#2E74B5;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	plays a role in a surgeon&#x2019;s decision to adopt the technology. We estimate that the national average incremental payment is approximately $500.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Unlike Medicare, commercial payors do not publish fee schedules. In general, based on selected feedback from facilities and surgeons, payments for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	insertion from the commercial payors who cover the procedure generally run somewhat higher than the comparable local Medicare payment.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Reimbursement for future products
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We have also filed and received approval of applications for CPT codes that describe our pipeline
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	devices. Our application for a CPT code to describe insertion of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent Supra
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	was approved by the American Medical Association, or AMA, in 2011 resulting in the creation of Category&nbsp;III CPT code 0253T. Our application for a CPT code to describe the insertion of additional trabecular meshwork stents (as with the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent Inject
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	procedure) was approved by the AMA in early 2014 resulting in the creation of Category&nbsp;III CPT code 0376T. While this code was available beginning on January&nbsp;1, 2015, for the reporting of procedures in which more than one
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	is inserted in the same eye, it currently does not result in any incremental facility or professional fee payment from Medicare. In addition, it is unclear whether any other third
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;party payor will cover the insertion of a second stent or that payment for a second stent will be adequate.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Reimbursement outside the United States
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Reimbursement in Europe
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In most of the developed European countries, healthcare is funded by the central government. In general, obtaining broad
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;based reimbursement and adequate payment for new technologies is more difficult in these markets than in the United States. As with the United States, high
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;quality published clinical data (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	i.e.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, randomized, controlled trials) is required to obtain coverage. However, most of the developed European countries require new medical technologies to not only be safe and effective, but also to be able to demonstrate clinical benefits that outweigh the costs when compared to the standard of care. Conversely, while some U.S. private insurers take cost into consideration, Medicare by law does not consider cost in its coverage decisions.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our primary focus has been on the U.S. market and we are in the early stages of commercialization in Europe. With regard to reimbursement in the larger developed countries, we have made the most progress in Germany. Prior to 2013, surgeons in Germany who implanted the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	used a code for a general glaucoma operation. This code was only payable in the hospital inpatient setting and, although the payment was sufficient to cover the cost of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and payment to the surgeon, the requirement of an overnight stay in the hospital was a significant barrier to adoption. Effective January&nbsp;1, 2013, there is a specific code (5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;133.9) describing implantation of a trabecular stent (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	e.g.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent Inject
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	). This code was added to the Einheitlicher Bewertungsma&#xDF;stab (EBM) or Unified Rating Scale of procedures that are payable in the outpatient setting. The 5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;133.9 code can be reported in conjunction with cataract surgery or as a stand
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;alone procedure. In addition, the payment to the surgeon for 5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;133.9 is considered adequate to cover the surgeon&#x2019;s costs (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	i.e.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, time) for inserting the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. Also, under the EBM, the cost of the implant can be passed through to the payor.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Although under German law healthcare is a universal right, and approximately 90% of the population is covered under the Statutory Health Insurance (SHI) or public plan, coverage decisions and payment are decentralized. Physicians who treat SHI patients must belong to a Kassen&#xE4;rztliche Vereinigung (KV) or Physician&#x2019;s Association. There are 17 KVs in Germany, and the KVs are responsible for negotiating the budget with the State Sickness Fund for physician and facility payments for outpatient procedures in their region. Generally, procedures that are added to the EBM are covered and paid for by the KVs; however, this is not automatic and the process of achieving routine payment for a new procedure listed on the EBM can take several months. With several KVs, an application must be made to the KV by a surgeon in that area who wishes to perform the procedure. In some cases, the addition of a new outpatient procedure can create budget issues and there can be a delay while the KV negotiates additional funds with the State Sickness Fund to cover payment for the new procedure.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	16
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<HR ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE='BACKGROUND-COLOR:#000000; BORDER-WIDTH:0; COLOR:#000000; HEIGHT:2PT; LINEHEIGHT:0; WIDTH:100%;'>
</HR>
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage20"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 30PT;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#GKOS-20151231X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#2E74B5;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Surgeons in each of the states continue to work to gain KV approval so that claims are processed smoothly. While the majority of claims submitted to KVs in 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	were
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	processed and paid, some
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	were
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	denied
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We are working with reimbursement consultants in Germany who have a successful track record of securing adequate payment for new medical technologies. In light of the strong favorable clinical data for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, we anticipate that reimbursement will continue to improve in Germany.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Under German law, if a person has an income above a certain level, that person can opt out of the SHI and obtain private insurance. Approximately 10% of Germans have opted out and are covered by private insurance companies. Each of these private insurance companies makes its own decisions on individual claims. In general, the private insurance companies cover and pay for outpatient procedures listed on the EBM and that has been our experience to date with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	insertion.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We have also made significant progress in reimbursement in Switzerland where the procedure that describes
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	insertion is on the list of approved outpatient procedures. This also means that the costs of any implants or supplies used during these procedures can be passed through for payment. Like Germany, coverage and payment decisions are decentralized, with 26 cantons and numerous private insurers determining coverage. To date, the vast majority of claims for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	procedures have been processed and paid with no issues.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In France, our application for a code to describe
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	insertion and our application to add the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	to the list of devices approved for pass through payment were denied in 2013. Following the publication of data on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent Inject
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, we submitted new applications for both devices in 2014. In November 2015, the French government approved the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	application for reimbursement. Unless there is a code and listing on the pass through list, the only opportunity for payment for the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in France would result from successful negotiations at the individual hospital level. There can be no assurance that the French government will approve pass through payment for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	even though
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	has been approved for reimbursement.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In the United Kingdom, Spain and Italy, there are no codes that specifically describe the insertion of a trabecular stent. We do not anticipate this changing in Spain and Italy in the near future. In addition, there is no mechanism to provide incremental payment for the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	when insertion is in conjunction with cataract surgery. Our success to date relies on our distributors in these countries negotiating with individual hospitals to cover the cost of inserting the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Reimbursement in other regions
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We currently market the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in Australia
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	New Zealand
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and Canada
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. In Australia, we have been successful at including the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent Inject
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	on the pass through list so that the cost of the device is paid separately. In New Zealand, the vast majority of the population is covered under a publicly
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;funded, universal
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;coverage health system, with services provided by public, private and non
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;governmental sectors.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	W
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	e have yet to achieve significant success with any of the public and major private payors
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in New Zealand
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In Canada, the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Inject
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	is paid through individual hospital budgets for glaucoma implants. We have yet to achieve a special funding pathway for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Inject
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in Canada and we will be subject to the limitation
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of individual hospital budgets until Canadian Provinces provide a special funding pathway for our products.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Although we are not yet commercial in Japan, we believe that the current reimbursement structure that would apply to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	insertion in conjunction with cataract surgery may support adequate reimbursement to both the facility and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	physician.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Competition
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We are positioning our products and MIGS procedures for use instead of, or in combination with, prescription eye drop therapies that currently dominate the glaucoma treatment marketplace. To a lesser extent, we also compete with manufacturers of medical devices used in other surgical therapy procedures for treating glaucoma, including laser as well as more complex and invasive
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	surgeries.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">

</FONT>
</P>

	greater experience in conducting research and development, manufacturing, clinical trials, preparing regulatory submissions and obtaining regulatory clearance or approval for drug and device products and marketing approved products.

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Companies with competing products include Alcon,&nbsp;Inc.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, a division of Novartis International
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	AG
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	(which has entered into a definitive agreement to acquire Transcend Medical, Inc.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	(Transcend)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, a MIGS competitor), Abbott Medical Optics&nbsp;Inc., Allergan&nbsp;plc (which has entered into a definitive merger agreement with Pfizer,&nbsp;Inc., pursuant to which the two companies intend to combine), STAAR Surgical Company, Lumenis&nbsp;Ltd., NeoMedix,Inc. and Ellex Medical Lasers Limited. Alcon,&nbsp;Inc. and Abbott Medical Optics&nbsp;Inc. are the leading manufacturers of aqueous shunts, and Alcon,&nbsp;Inc. also markets the EX
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;PRESS Glaucoma Filtration Device and, upon its completion of the Transcend acquisition, will be a manufacturer of a MIGS device. Lumenis&nbsp;Ltd. is a leading manufacturer of SLT equipment. Neo
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	M
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	edix,&nbsp;Inc. markets an electrosurgical device and Ellex Medical Lasers Limited markets a canaloplasty device that some physicians employ to lower intraocular pressure in glaucoma.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In addition to these current competitors, we may also in the future compete with manufacturers of alternative technologies to treat glaucoma. We are aware of several companies, including Transcend (which has entered into a definitive agreement to be acquired by Alcon, Inc
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	), AqueSys,&nbsp;Inc. (which was recently acquired by Allergan&nbsp;plc, a publicly traded company, which has entered into a definitive merger agreement with Pfizer,&nbsp;Inc., pursuant to which the two companies intend to combine), InnFocus&nbsp;Inc. and Ivantis&nbsp;Inc.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	that are conducting FDA
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;approved IDE clinical trials or have filed for regulatory approval of MIGS devices. These products or other products that may be developed could demonstrate better safety or effectiveness, clinical results, ease of use or lower costs than our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	or other products under development. If approved for marketing, these devices may compete directly with the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and our products under development. If any of these alternative technologies gain market acceptance, this may reduce demand for our primary product, the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, as well as for our products in development
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In addition to competing for market share for our products, we also compete against these companies for personnel, including qualified sales representatives that are necessary to grow our business, as well as scientific and clinical personnel from universities and research institutions that are important to our research and development efforts.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We believe the principal competitive factors in our market include:
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 17.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">
	&#xB7;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;WIDTH:1PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	improved outcomes for glaucoma;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:36PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 17.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">
	&#xB7;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:1PT;">

	acceptance by ophthalmic surgeons;
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 30PT;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
