<EFX_MANAGEMENTS_DISCUSSION>
<A NAME="FIS_MANAGEMENTS_DISCUSSION"></A>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;PUNCTUATION-WRAP:HANGING;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	ITEM
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 36PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	MANAGEMENT&#x2019;S DISCUSSION
</FONT>
<A NAME="GKOS-20151231X10K_HTM_ITEM7MANAGEMENTSDISCUSSION_342697">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	AND ANALYSIS OF FINANCIAL COND
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	ITION AND RESULTS OF OPERATIONS
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	You should read the following discussion and analysis of our financial condition and results of operations together with &#x201C;Selected financial data&#x201D; and our audited consolidated financial statements and related notes included in Items 6 and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&nbsp;8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	, respectively, of this Annual Report on Form 10-K.&nbsp;&nbsp;This discussion and analysis and other parts of this Annual Report on Form 10-K contain forward looking statements that reflect our current plans, expectations, estimates and beliefs that involve risks, uncertainties and assumptions, such as statements regarding our plans, objectives, expectations, intentions and projections. Our actual results and the timing of selected events may differ materially from those discussed in these forward looking statements. You should carefully read Item 1A - &#x201C;Risk Factors&#x201D; included in this Annual Report on Form 10-K to gain an understanding of the important factors that could cause actual results to differ materially from our forward looking statements. Please also see the section entitled &#x201C;Special Note Regarding Forward Looking Statements and Industry Data.&#x201D;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	Overview
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We are an ophthalmic medical technology company focused on the development and commercialization of breakthrough products and procedures designed to transform the treatment of glaucoma, one of the world&#x2019;s leading causes of blindness. We have pioneered Micro
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;Invasive Glaucoma Surgery, or MIGS, to revolutionize the traditional glaucoma treatment and management paradigm. We launched the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, our first MIGS device, in the United States in July 2012 and we are leveraging our platform technology to build a comprehensive and proprietary portfolio of micro
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;scale injectable therapies designed to address the complete range of glaucoma disease states and progression.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	is the first commercially available MIGS treatment solution. FDA
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;approved for insertion in combination with cataract surgery, the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	has been shown to lower intraocular pressure in adult patients with mild
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;moderate open
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;angle glaucoma, which represents the majority of glaucoma cases. The
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	procedure is currently reimbursed by Medicare and a majority of commercial payors.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We are building a broad portfolio of micro
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;scale injectable therapies designed to address the complete range of glaucoma disease states and progression, including three innovative pipeline products: the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent Inject
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent Supra
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iDose
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. The
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent Inject
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	includes two stents pre
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;loaded in an auto
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;injection inserter. We are developing two versions of this product: the first is currently being studied for lowering intraocular pressure in conjunction with cataract surgery in a U.S. investigational device exemption, or IDE, pivotal trial; the second is currently being studied in an initial U.S. IDE study as a standalone treatment for lowering intraocular pressure. This second version is also capable of making its own self
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;sealing corneal penetration, potentially offering patient treatment in a minor surgical suite or an in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;office setting. The
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent Supra
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	is designed to access an alternative drainage space within the eye where we estimate 20% of aqueous humor outflow occurs, and is now in a U.S. pivotal IDE trial.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iDose
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	is an implant that is designed to provide a sustained release of a prostaglandin drug to lower intraocular pressure in glaucoma patients. To validate the safety and efficacy of our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	products, we are currently conducting 17 prospective clinical trials.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We have never been profitable and have incurred operating losses in each year since our inception
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our net sales increased to $71.7&nbsp;million in 2015 from $45.6&nbsp;million in 2014 and $20.9 million in 2013, and our net losses were $38.3&nbsp;million, $14.1&nbsp;million and $14.2 million for the years ended December&nbsp;31, 2015, 2014 and 2013, respectively
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. As of December 31, 2015, we had an accumulated deficit of $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	196.6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We have made and expect to continue to make significant investments in our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	global
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	sales force and marketing programs.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Costs for FDA
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;approved IDE studies in our industry are expensive as are the costs to develop new products, and we expect to incur a significant increase in administrative costs as we begin operating as a public company. While the gross profits from our growing net sales will help offset some of these costs, we expect to invest significantly more resources into our business using proceeds from the IPO, that we completed on June&nbsp;30, 2015. Accordingly, we expect to continue to experience net losses for the foreseeable future.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">

<A NAME="eolPage78"></A>

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 30PT;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#GKOS-20151231X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#2E74B5;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	On June&nbsp;30, 2015, we completed our IPO, selling 6.9&nbsp;million newly issued shares of common stock at a price of $18.00 per share, pursuant to a Registration Statement on Form&nbsp;S
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;1 that was declared effective on June&nbsp;24, 2015. The IPO generated net proceeds of approximately $113.6&nbsp;million, after deducting underwriting discounts and commissions of $8.7&nbsp;million and other related expenses of approximately $1.9&nbsp;million. At December 31, 2015, we had cash, cash equivalents and short-term investments of $91.1&nbsp;million. We may seek to obtain additional financing in the future through the issuance of our common stock, through other equity or debt financings, through collaborations or partnerships with other companies or through non
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;dilutive financing. We may not be able to raise additional capital on terms acceptable to us, or at all, and any failure to raise capital as and when needed could materially harm our business, results of operations and future business prospects, including our ability to continue as a going concern. We believe that our existing cash, cash equivalents and short-term investments will be sufficient to fund our operations for at least the next 12 months
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	Factors affecting future results
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In January 2007, we entered into an agreement with GMP Vision Solutions
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Inc.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, or GMP, to acquire certain in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;process research and development and therein agreed to make periodic royalty payments to GMP. In December 2012, we paid GMP $1.0&nbsp;million for a 90
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;day option to buy out all of the remaining royalties payable to GMP under the January 2007 agreement. We did not exercise the option, which expired in April 2013.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In November 2013, we amended the agreement and entered into a royalty buyout agreement with GMP pursuant to which we bought out all of the remaining royalties payable to GMP in exchange for the issuance of an aggregate of $17.5&nbsp;million in secured promissory notes payable to GMP and a party related to GMP. In connection with this buyout agreement, we recognized an intangible asset valued at $17.5&nbsp;million, which is being amortized to cost of sales on a straight
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;line basis by year as follows: $0.5&nbsp;million in 2013, $3.5&nbsp;million in each of 2014, 2015, 2016 and 2017 and $3.0&nbsp;million in 2018. The notes required monthly interest
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;only payments through December&nbsp;31, 2014, followed by 24 equal monthly principal and interest payments of $0.8&nbsp;million, which we began paying on January&nbsp;31, 2015 and will pay through December&nbsp;31, 2016. Accordingly, our cost of sales will be impacted through 2018 as a result of the amortization and our cash flows will be adversely affected by the debt service costs, primarily in 2015 and 2016 when principal payments are required in addition to interest. The terms of the subordinated notes are more fully described below under &#x201C;&#x2014;Liquidity and capital resources&#x2014;indebtedness.&#x201D;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In December 2014, we entered into an agreement with The Regents of the University of California, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	University
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, to correct inventorship in connection with a group of our U.S. patent rights and to obtain from the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	University
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	a covenant that it did not and would not claim any right or title to such patent rights and will not challenge or assist any others in challenging such patent rights. In connection with the agreement, we agreed to pay to the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	University
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	the sum of $2.7&nbsp;million in five payments during 2015 as follows: $500,000 by January&nbsp;30, 2015; $125,000 by March&nbsp;31, 2015; $250,000 by June&nbsp;30, 2015; $250,000 by September&nbsp;30, 2015; and $1,575,000 by December&nbsp;31, 2015. Under the terms of the agreement, the payments were due within 60&nbsp;days of our IPO, and, accordingly, we paid the balance due of $1,825,000 prior to August&nbsp;29, 2015. We accrued the $2.7&nbsp;million obligation, net of imputed interest of $0.1&nbsp;million, as of December&nbsp;31, 2014, and charged it to cost of sales in the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2014. In addition, beginning with sales on or after January&nbsp;1, 2015, we agreed to pay the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	University
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	a payment equal to a low
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;single digit percentage of worldwide net sales of certain current and future products, including our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	products, with a required minimum annual payment of $500,000. The ongoing royalty payment terminates on the date that the last of the patent rights expires, which is currently expected to be in 2022.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In February 2015, we and our primary bank executed an Amended and Restated Revolving Credit and Term Loan Agreement, or the Amended Credit Agreement, which provided for a $5.0&nbsp;million senior secured term loan, a $5.0&nbsp;million senior secured draw
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;to term loan and an $8.0&nbsp;million senior secured revolving credit facility. The senior secured term loan and draw
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;to term loan would have matured and would have been required to be fully paid by February&nbsp;23, 2019. On the closing date, we received $5.0&nbsp;million cash under the senior secured term loan. The entire unpaid principal amount plus any accrued but unpaid interest under the revolving line of credit was due to become payable in full on February&nbsp;23, 2017. As of July&nbsp;31, 2015 we had drawn $2.0&nbsp;million under the draw
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;to term loan. On July&nbsp;31, 2015, we paid off all amounts outstanding under the Amended Credit Agreement with the payment of $7.0&nbsp;million in principal plus all interest and fees payable through the payoff date, and recorded a loss on extinguishment
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">

<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>

</FONT>

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of debt in the amount of $0.2&nbsp;million. The Amended Credit Agreement and all related security interests were terminated on July&nbsp;31, 2015. The agreements with our primary bank are more fully described under &#x201C;&#x2014;Liquidity and capital resources&#x2014;indebtedness.&#x201D;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	Components of results of operations
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Net sales
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We operate in one reportable segment and substantially all of our net sales are derived from sales of our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	products, net of customer returns and allowances. We recognize net sales when goods are shipped, title and risk of loss transfer to our customers, persuasive evidence of an arrangement exists and collectability is reasonably assured.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We sell our products through a direct sales organization in the United States, and outside the United States we sell our products primarily through independent distributors
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and through direct sales subsidiaries in some countries
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. The primary end
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;user customers for our products are hospitals and surgery centers.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We anticipate our net sales will increase as we expand our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	global
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	sales and marketing infrastructure and continue to increase awareness of our products by expanding our sales base and increasing our marketing efforts. We also expect that our net sales within a fiscal year may be impacted seasonally and reflect seasonality patterns generally consistent with U.S. cataract procedure volumes, which are typically softer in the first quarter and stronger in the fourth quarter of a given year
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Cost of sales
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Cost of sales reflects the aggregate costs to manufacture our products and includes raw material costs, labor costs, manufacturing overhead expenses and the effect of changes in the balance of reserves for excess and obsolete inventory. We manufacture our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	products at our headquarters in Laguna Hills, California using components manufactured by third parties. Due to the relatively low production volumes of our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	products, compared to our potential capacity for those products, a significant portion of our per unit costs is comprised of manufacturing overhead expenses. These expenses include quality assurance, material procurement, inventory control, facilities, equipment and operations supervision and management.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Beginning in late 2013, cost of sales has included amortization of the $17.5&nbsp;million intangible asset we recognized in connection with our royalty buyout agreement with GMP in November 2013. The amortization expense was $3.5&nbsp;million, $3.5&nbsp;million and $0.5&nbsp;million in the years ended December&nbsp;31, 2015, 2014 and 2013 and is estimated to be $3.5&nbsp;million in each of 2016 and 2017, and $3.0&nbsp;million in 2018.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Beginning in 2015, cost of sales includes a charge equal to a low single
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;digit percentage of worldwide net sales of certain current and future products, including our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	products, with a required minimum annual payment of $500,000, which amount became payable to the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	University
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in connection with our December 2014 agreement. This obligation will expire upon the expiration of the last to expire of the patent rights that are the subject of the December 2014 agreement, which is currently expected to be in 2022. Additionally, as a medical device manufacturer, we are required to pay the 2.3% federal medical device excise tax on U.S. sales of medical devices manufactured by us. Under the PATH Act, this tax has been suspended from January&nbsp;1, 2016, to December&nbsp;31, 2017, and, absent further legislative action, will be reinstated starting January&nbsp;1, 2018. The medical device excise tax is included in our cost of sales
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in 2015, 2014 and 2013
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our future gross profit as a percentage of net sales, or gross margin, will be impacted by numerous factors including commencement of sales of products in our pipeline, or any other future products, which may have higher product costs. Our gross margin will also be affected by manufacturing inefficiencies that we may experience as we attempt to manufacture our products on a larger scale, manufacture new products and change our manufacturing capacity or output. Additionally, our gross margin will continue to be affected by the aforementioned intangible asset amortization, expense related to our agreement with the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	University
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. We also expect our gross margin to be
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	favorably
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	76
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">

<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage80"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 30PT;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#GKOS-20151231X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#2E74B5;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	impacted by the Consolidated Appropriations Act of 2016 moratorium for 2016 and 2017 on the medical device excise tax.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Selling, general and administrative
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our selling, general and administrative, or SG&amp;A, expenses primarily consist of personnel
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;related expenses, including salaries, sales commissions, bonuses, fringe benefits and stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;based compensation for our executive, financial, marketing, sales, business development and administrative functions. Other significant SG&amp;A expenses include marketing programs, advertising, conferences and congresses, and travel expenses, as well as the costs associated with obtaining and maintaining our patent portfolio, professional fees for accounting, auditing, consulting and legal services, travel and allocated overhead expenses.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We expect SG&amp;A expenses to continue to grow as we increase our sales
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	marketing
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	infrastructure globally and our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	clinical education and general administration infrastructure in the United States. We also expect other nonemployee
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;related costs, including sales and marketing program activities for new products, outside services and accounting and general legal costs to increase as our overall operations grow. The timing of these increased expenditures and their magnitude are primarily dependent on the commercial success and sales growth of our products, as well as on the timing of any new product launches. In addition, we have begun to incur increased SG&amp;A expenses resulting from becoming a public company, which may further increase when we are no longer able to rely on certain &#x201C;emerging growth company&#x201D; exemptions we are afforded under the Jumpstart Our Business Startups Act, or the JOBS Act.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Research and development
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our research and development, or R&amp;D, activities primarily consist of new product development projects, pre
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;clinical studies, IDE studies, and other clinical trials. Our R&amp;D expenses primarily consist of personnel
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;related expenses, including salaries, fringe benefits and stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;based compensation for our R&amp;D employees; research materials; supplies and services; and the costs of conducting clinical studies, which include payments to investigational sites and investigators, clinical research organizations, consultants, and other outside technical services and the costs of materials, supplies and travel. We expense R&amp;D costs as incurred. We expect our R&amp;D expenses to increase as we initiate and advance our development programs, the most costly of which are expected to be our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent Inject
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent Supra
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iDose
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	product candidates.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Completion dates and costs for our clinical development programs including seeking regulatory approvals, and our research programs can vary significantly for each current and future product candidate and are difficult to predict. As a result, while we expect our R&amp;D costs to continue to increase for the foreseeable future, we cannot estimate with any degree of certainty the costs we will incur in connection with the development of our product candidates. We anticipate we will make determinations as to which programs and product candidates to pursue and how much funding to direct to each program and product candidate on an ongoing basis in response to the scientific success of early research programs, results of ongoing and future clinical trials, as well as ongoing assessments as to each current or future product candidate&#x2019;s commercial potential and our likelihood of obtaining necessary regulatory approvals.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Other (expense) income, net
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Other (expense) income, net primarily consists of interest expense on our Amended Credit Agreement and our secured promissory notes payable to GMP and a party related to GMP as well as changes in the fair value of our stock warrant liability. On July&nbsp;31, 2015, we paid off in full all amounts outstanding under the Amended Credit Agreement and terminated the agreement, and recorded a loss on extinguishment of debt in other (expense) income.&nbsp;&nbsp;In 2015, other (expense) income also included the loss on deconsolidation of DOSE
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">

<FONT SIZE="1">

</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Net sales
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Net sales for the years ended December 31, 2015 and 2014 were $71.7&nbsp;million and $45.6&nbsp;million, respectively, reflecting an increase of $26.1&nbsp;million or 57%, with net sales in the United States representing $67.7&nbsp;million and $42.9&nbsp;million of net sales, respectively, and accounting for 95% of the overall increase. Our average number of domestic sales representatives increased to 45 for the year ended December 31, 2015 from 35 for the year ended December 31, 2014. The higher number of sales representatives helped increase our customer base, leading to growth in unit sales. Increased unit volume was responsible for the majority of the increase in net sales
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Cost of sales
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Cost of sales for the years ended December 31, 2015 and 2014 were $13.0&nbsp;million and $11.4&nbsp;million, respectively, reflecting an increase of $1.6&nbsp;million or 14%. Our gross margin for the year ended December 31, 2015 was approximately 82% compared to approximately 75%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2014. In 2014, cost of sales included a charge of $2.6 million, or 6% of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	sales, associated with our December 2014 agreement with the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	University
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	which
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	accounted for the majority of the improvement in our gross margin
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Selling, general and administrative expenses
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	SG&amp;A expenses for the years ended December 31, 2015 and 2014 were $44.0&nbsp;million and $28.1&nbsp;million, respectively, reflecting an increase of $15.9&nbsp;million or 56%. Stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;based compensation expense increased by $4.7&nbsp;million, which included a charge of $2.8&nbsp;million for the recording of cumulative stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;based compensation expense associated with stock options we granted in July 2014 containing a performance condition that was satisfied upon the completion of our IPO. The remaining increase in SG&amp;A expenses was primarily the result of an increase of approximately $4.6&nbsp;million in personnel, travel and other costs associated with our expanding domestic sales force; an increase of approximately $2.3&nbsp;million for additional administrative and marketing personnel; an increase of approximately $2.1&nbsp;million in legal fees primarily associated with our patent litigation; and an increase in SG&amp;A expenses incurred by our foreign subsidiaries of approximately $1.2 million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Research and development expenses

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	R&amp;D expenses for the years ended December 31, 2015 and 2014 were $25.0&nbsp;million and $19.2&nbsp;million, respectively, reflecting an increase of $5.8&nbsp;million or 30%. Payroll and related expenses increased by approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$3.2&nbsp;million due to the cost of additional personnel, primarily in our clinical affairs function, required to manage the increased number of clinical studies and associated investigational sites and study investigators. Stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;based compensation expense increased by $1.5&nbsp;million, which included a charge of $0.9&nbsp;million for the recording of cumulative stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;based compensation expense associated with stock options we granted in July 2014 containing a performance condition that was satisfied upon the completion of our IPO. The remaining increase in R&amp;D expenses resulted primarily from higher clinical study costs, which included payments to investigational sites and study investigators, consultants, and other outside technical service providers and the costs of related materials, supplies and travel
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Other (expense) income, net
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We recorded other expense, net for the years ended December 31, 2015 and 2014 of approximately $28.0&nbsp;million and $0.9&nbsp;million, respectively, reflecting an increase of $27.1&nbsp;million. The 2015 period includes a charge of $25.7&nbsp;million incurred with the deconsolidation of the non
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;glaucoma related assets of DOSE and elimination of the noncontrolling interest. See &#x201C;&#x2014;Critical accounting policies and significant estimates&#x2014;DOSE&#x2014;variable interest entity accounting
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.&#x201D;
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Net sales
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Net sales for the years ended December&nbsp;31, 2014 and 2013 were $45.6&nbsp;million and $20.9&nbsp;million, respectively, reflecting an increase of $24.7&nbsp;million or 118%, with net sales in the United States representing $42.9&nbsp;million and $19.5&nbsp;million, respectively, and accounting for 95% of the increase. The increase in net sales was primarily attributable to an increase in the number of sales representatives and increased reimbursement coverage, which together led to an increase in unit sales growth. Our average number of sales representatives increased to 35 in 2014 from 22 in 2013. Increased unit volume accounted for approximately 98% of the increase in net sales, and approximately 2% of the increase in net sales resulted from an increase in average selling prices.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Cost of sales
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Cost of sales for the years ended December&nbsp;31, 2014 and 2013 were $11.4&nbsp;million and $2.5&nbsp;million, respectively, reflecting an increase of $8.9&nbsp;million or 350%. Our gross margin for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2014 was approximately 75% compared to approximately 88% in the same period of 2013. Cost of sales in 2014 includes a $2.6&nbsp;million charge associated with our December 2014 agreement with the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	University
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and $3.5&nbsp;million of intangible asset amortization, which together totaled $6.1&nbsp;million or approximately 13% of 2014 net sales. Amortization of the intangible asset commenced late in 2013 and $0.5&nbsp;million was recorded in cost of sales for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2013, representing less than 3% of 2013 net sales. The increase in intangible asset amortization and the charge associated
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	with the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	University
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	agreement together account for 11% of the 13% reduction in gross margin for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2014 as compared to the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2013.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Selling, general and administrative expenses
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	SG&amp;A expenses for the years ended December&nbsp;31, 2014 and 2013 were $28.1&nbsp;million and $17.1&nbsp;million, respectively, reflecting an increase of $11.0&nbsp;million or 65%. The increase in SG&amp;A expenses was primarily the result of an increase of approximately $4.4&nbsp;million in personnel, travel and other costs associated with our expanding domestic sales force; an increase of approximately $1.9&nbsp;million in legal fees primarily associated with our patent litigation; an increase of approximately $1.2&nbsp;million in SG&amp;A expenses incurred by our subsidiary in Germany; and approximately $1.2&nbsp;million in costs in 2014 related to our efforts to prepare for our initial public offering.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Research and development expenses
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	R&amp;D expenses for the years ended December&nbsp;31, 2014 and 2013 were $19.2&nbsp;million and $15.5&nbsp;million, respectively, reflecting an increase of $3.7&nbsp;million or 24%. The increase resulted primarily from higher clinical study costs, which included payments to investigational sites and investigators, consultants, and other outside technical service providers and the costs of related materials, supplies and travel. Our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	I
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	nject
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	clinical study enrolled significantly more subjects in 2014 as compared to 2013, and was the largest single contributor to the expense increase.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Other expense, net
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We recorded other expense, net for the years ended December&nbsp;31, 2014 and 2013 of approximately $0.9&nbsp;million and $23,000, respectively. The increase was primarily the result of interest expense on our subordinated debt issued in November 2013.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 7PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	Liquidity and capital resources
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Since our inception, we have incurred losses and negative cash flow from our operations and, as of December 31, 2015, we had an accumulated deficit of approximately $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	196.6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million. We have funded our operations to date from the sale of equity securities, issuance of notes payable, cash exercises of stock options and warrants to purchase equity securities and cash generated from net sales, and on June&nbsp;30, 2015, we completed our IPO, selling 6.9&nbsp;million newly issued shares of common stock at $18.00 per share, which raised net proceeds of approximately $113.6&nbsp;million, after deducting underwriting discounts and commissions of $8.7&nbsp;million and other related expenses of approximately $1.9&nbsp;million. We have made and expect to continue to make significant investments in our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	global
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	sales force and marketing programs. Costs for FDA
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;approved IDE studies in our industry are expensive as are the costs to develop new products, and we have begun to incur a significant increase in administrative costs as we operate as a public company. We expect to invest significantly more resources into our business using proceeds from the IPO. Accordingly, we expect to continue to experience net losses for the foreseeable future and expect that our sales performance will significantly impact our cash management decisions.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	At December 31, 2015, we had $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	91.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million in cash
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	cash equivalents
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and short-term investments
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. We believe that our available cash, cash equivalents, investment balances and interest we earn on these balances and cash generated from sales of our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	products will be sufficient to satisfy our liquidity requirements for at least the next 12 months.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 7PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	Cash flows
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Our historical cash outflows have primarily been associated with cash used for operating activities such as the purchase and growth of inventory, expansion of our sales and marketing and R&amp;D activities and other working capital needs; the acquisition of intellectual property; and expenditures related to equipment and improvements used to increase our manufacturing capacity, and improve our manufacturing efficiency and for overall facility expansion.
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million, $7.1&nbsp;million and $13.3 million, respectively, of net cash in operating activities. The decrease in net cash used in operating activities primarily reflects an increase in cash generated from significantly higher net sales of our

	iStent

	3.4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	39.5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million. For the year ended December 31, 2014, the total net change in operating assets and liabilities provided cash of $1.2&nbsp;million, as growth in accounts payable and accrued liabilities exceeded the combined growth in accounts receivable and inventory. Additionally, net non
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;cash operating costs totaled $5.7&nbsp;million. For the year ended December 31, 2013, the total net change in operating assets and liabilities used cash of $1.4&nbsp;million due to increases in accounts receivable and inventory, partially offset by an increase in accounts payable. More than offsetting this amount were net non

</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	Indebtedness
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Notes payable to GMP Vision Solutions
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In November 2013, we amended the agreement originally entered into with GMP in January 2007 and executed a royalty buyout agreement with GMP pursuant to which we issued an aggregate of $17.5&nbsp;million in secured promissory notes to GMP and a party related to GMP in exchange for the cancellation of remaining royalties payable to GMP under the original agreement. These notes are secured by all of our assets, excluding intellectual property, and were previously subordinate to the rights of our bank lender in connection with our Amended Credit Agreement, described below prior to the repayment in full of that facility. The notes carry an interest rate of 5% per annum and required monthly interest
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;only payments from November&nbsp;30, 2013 through December&nbsp;31, 2014 of $72,900, followed by 24 equal monthly principal and interest payments of $0.8&nbsp;million, which we began paying on January&nbsp;31, 2015 and will pay through December&nbsp;31, 2016. We concluded that the transaction resulted in the recognition of a $17.5&nbsp;million intangible asset. After determining that the pattern of future cash flows associated with this intangible asset could not be reliably estimated with a high level of precision, we concluded that the intangible asset will be amortized to cost of sales in our statements of operations on a straight line basis over the estimated useful life of five years.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In the years ended December&nbsp;31, 2015, 2014 and 2013, we recorded related amortization expense of $3.5&nbsp;million, $3.5&nbsp;million and $0.5&nbsp;million, respectively, in cost of sales. Estimated amortization expense will be $3.5&nbsp;million in each of 2016 and 2017, and $3.0&nbsp;million in 2018.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Amended and Restated Revolving Credit and Term Loan Agreement
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In June 2013, we entered into a loan and security agreement, or Credit Agreement, with our primary bank for a line of credit in the maximum principal amount of $6.0&nbsp;million. Advances under the Credit Agreement were limited to the lesser of (i)&nbsp;$6.0&nbsp;million or (ii)&nbsp;77% of the sum of cash, cash equivalents and eligible domestic accounts receivable. The entire unpaid principal amount plus any accrued but unpaid interest was due to become payable in full on June&nbsp;5, 2015. Obligations under the line of credit bore interest on the outstanding daily balance thereof at the bank&#x2019;s prime rate plus 0.5% (3.75% at December&nbsp;31, 2014). Amounts owed were secured by a first priority security interest in all of our assets, excluding intellectual property. Additionally, the terms of the Credit Agreement contained various affirmative and negative covenants. There was $1.9&nbsp;million outstanding under this line of credit as of December&nbsp;31, 2014.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In February 2015, we and our primary bank executed the Amended Credit Agreement, which provided for a $5.0&nbsp;million senior secured term loan, a $5.0&nbsp;million senior secured draw
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;to term loan and an $8.0&nbsp;million senior secured revolving credit facility. Amounts owed under the Amended Credit Agreement were secured by a first priority security interest in all of our assets, excluding intellectual property. We were required to comply with certain non
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;financial and financial covenants as provided in the Amended Credit Agreement that, if not met, could have constituted events of default. We were in compliance with all such covenants through the payoff date.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	On the closing date, we received $5.0&nbsp;million cash under the senior secured term loan and immediately paid off the $2.1&nbsp;million balance outstanding under the line of credit. This loan required quarterly principal payments of $0.4&nbsp;million over a three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;year period beginning May&nbsp;1, 2016 and was to mature February&nbsp;23, 2019. The senior secured draw
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;to term loan was to be available through February&nbsp;23, 2016 for advances up to an aggregate of $5.0&nbsp;million, and required quarterly principal payments equal to 1/12 of the aggregate principal amount over a three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;year period beginning May&nbsp;1, 2016 and was to mature February&nbsp;23, 2019. Prior to our repayment of the term loan described below, we had drawn $2.0&nbsp;million under the draw
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;to term loan. Advances under the revolving line of credit were limited to the lesser of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	(i)&nbsp;$8.0&nbsp;million or (ii)&nbsp;a calculated borrowing base consisting of (a)&nbsp;80% of eligible accounts receivable plus (b)&nbsp;the lesser of 30% of eligible inventory or $1.5&nbsp;million. The entire unpaid principal amount plus any accrued but unpaid interest under the revolving line of credit was due to become payable in full on February&nbsp;23, 2017.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Outstanding balances under the senior secured term loan and senior secured draw
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;to term loan bore interest on the outstanding daily balance thereof at an annual percentage rate equal to the bank&#x2019;s prime rate plus 2%. At our option, all or a portion of the amounts owed under any of the senior secured term loan and draw
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;to term loan may have been converted into Eurodollar
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;based advances at an annual percentage rate equal to LIBOR plus 3%. Outstanding balances under the revolving credit facility bore interest on the outstanding daily balance thereof at an annual percentage rate equal to the bank&#x2019;s prime rate plus 1.75%. At our option, all or a portion of the amounts owed under the revolving credit facility may have been converted into Eurodollar
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;based advances at an annual percentage rate equal to LIBOR plus 2.75%. In connection with the execution of the Amended Credit Agreement, we issued warrants to the lenders to purchase an aggregate of 11,298 shares of common stock at an exercise price of $8.85 per share.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	On July&nbsp;31, 2015, we paid off in full all amounts outstanding under the Amended Credit Agreement with the payment of $7.0&nbsp;million in principal plus all interest and fees payable through the payoff date and recorded a loss on extinguishment of debt in the amount of $0.2&nbsp;million. The Amended Credit Agreement and all related security interests were terminated on July&nbsp;31, 2015. Accordingly, this facility is no longer outstanding and available to us.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	There were
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	no
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	material commitments for capital expenditures as of December 31, 2015.
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	Off
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&#8209;balance sheet arrangements
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We do not have any off
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;balance sheet arrangements as defined in the rules and regulations of the SEC. We do not have any relationships with unconsolidated entities or financial partnerships, such as entities often referred to as structured finance or special purpose entities, which would have been established for the purpose of facilitating off
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;balance sheet arrangements or for any other contractually narrow or limited purpose. However, from time to time we enter into certain types of contracts that contingently require us to indemnify parties against third
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;party claims including in connection with certain real estate leases, and supply purchase agreements, and with directors and officers. The terms of such obligations vary by contract and in most instances a maximum dollar amount is not explicitly stated therein. Generally, amounts under these contracts cannot by reasonably estimated until a specific claim is asserted, thus no liabilities have been recorded for these obligations on our balance sheets for any of the periods presented.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	Inflation
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We may experience pressure on our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	selling prices resulting from potential future reductions in reimbursement payments to our customers, particularly from governmental payors such as Medicare or Medicaid but also from private payors. We could also be impacted by risi
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ng costs for certain inflation
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	sensitive operating expenses such as labor and employee benefits. However, we do not believe that inflation has had a material effect on our business, financial condition or results of operations presented herein. If our costs were to become subject to significant
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">

</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 30PT;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	inflationary pressures, we may not be able to fully offset such higher costs through selling price increases. Our inability or failure to do so could adversely affect our business, financial condition and results of operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	Critical accounting policies and significant estimates
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Management&#x2019;s discussion and analysis of our financial condition and results of operations are based on our financial statements, which have been prepared in accordance with U.S. generally accepted accounting principles, or GAAP. The preparation of these financial statements requires us to make estimates and judgments that affect the reported amounts of assets and liabilities and related disclosure of contingent assets and liabilities, revenue and expenses at the date of the financial statements. Generally, we base our estimates on historical experience and on various other assumptions in accordance with GAAP that we believe to be reasonable under the circumstances. Actual results may differ
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	materially
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	from these estimates under different assumptions or conditions and such differences could be material to our financial position and results of operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	While our significant accounting policies are more fully described in the Notes to our consolidated financial statements appearing elsewhere in this
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Annual Report on Form 10-K
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, we believe the following accounting policies to be most critical for fully understanding and evaluating our financial condition and results of operations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Revenue recognition
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We generate revenue primarily from sales of our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	products. We recognize revenue from product sales when the following criteria are met: goods are shipped, title and risk of loss has transferred to our customers, persuasive evidence of an arrangement exists and collectability is reasonably assured. Persuasive evidence of an arrangement exists when we have a contractual arrangement in place with the customer. Delivery has occurred when a product is shipped. If persuasive evidence of an arrangement exists and delivery has occurred, we determine whether the invoiced amount is fixed or determinable and collectability of the invoiced amount is reasonably assured. We assess whether the invoiced amount is fixed or determinable based on the existing arrangement with the customer, including whether we have sufficient history with a customer to reliably estimate the customer&#x2019;s payment patterns. We assess collectability by evaluating historical cash receipts and individual customer outstanding balances. To the extent all criteria set forth above are not satisfied at the time of shipment, revenue is recognized when cash is received from the customer.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We permit returns of product if such product is returned in good condition and from normal distribution channels. Estimated allowances for sales returns are based upon the historical patterns of our product returns matched against sales, and our evaluation of specific factors that may increase the risk of product returns. Product returns to date have been immaterial.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Clinical trial expense accruals
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	As part of our R&amp;D expenses, we accrue at each balance sheet date the estimated costs of clinical study activities performed by third
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;party clinical sites with whom we have agreements providing for fees based upon the quantities of subjects enrolled and clinical evaluation visits that occur over the life of the study. The estimates are determined based upon a review of the agreements and data collected by internal and external clinical personnel as to the status of enrollment and subject visits, and are based upon the facts and circumstances known to us at each financial reporting date. If the actual timing of performance of activities varies from the assumptions used in the estimates, we adjust the accruals accordingly. There have been no material adjustments to our prior period accrued estimates for clinical trial activities through December 31, 2015. If we underestimate or overestimate the activity or fees associated with a study or service at a given point in time, adjustments to R&amp;D expenses may be necessary in future periods. Subsequent changes in estimates may result in a material change in our accruals. Nonrefundable advance payments for goods and services, including fees for process development or manufacturing and distribution of clinical supplies that will be used in future research and development activities, are deferred and recognized as expense in the period that the related goods are consumed or services are performed.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	84
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<HR ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE='BACKGROUND-COLOR:#000000; BORDER-WIDTH:0; COLOR:#000000; HEIGHT:2PT; LINEHEIGHT:0; WIDTH:100%;'>
</HR>
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage88"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 30PT;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#GKOS-20151231X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#2E74B5;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Inventory valuation
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	We value inventory at the lower of cost or market (net realizable value). Cost is determined by the first
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;in, first
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;out method. This policy requires us to make estimates regarding the market value of our inventory, including an assessment of excess or obsolete inventory. We evaluate inventory for excess quantities and obsolescence based on an estimate of the future demand for our product within a specified time horizon, and record an allowance to reduce the carrying value of inventory as determined necessary. The estimates we use for demand are also used for near
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;term capacity planning and inventory purchasing and are consistent with our revenue forecasts. If our actual demand is less than our forecast demand, we may be required to take additional excess inventory charges, which would decrease gross margin and adversely impact net operating results in the future.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#8209;based compensation expense
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;based compensation expense is measured at the date of grant, based on the estimated fair value of the award using the Black
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;Scholes option pricing model. For awards subject to time
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;based vesting
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	conditions, we recognize stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	based compensation expense over the employee&#x2019;s requisite service period on a straight
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;line basis, net of estimated for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	feitures. We account for stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	based compensation arrangements with non
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;employees using a fair value approach. Stock options granted to non
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;employees are subject to periodic revaluation over their vesting terms.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The estimation of the fair value of each stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;based grant or issuance on the date of grant involves numerous assumptions by management. Although we calculate the fair value under the Black
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;Scholes option pricing model, which is a standard option pricing model, this model still requires the use of numerous assumptions, including, among others, the expected life (turnover), volatility of the underlying equity security, a risk free interest rate and expected dividends. We do not have publicly traded equity and have a limited operating history and a lack of company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;specific historical and implied volatility data, and therefore we have estimated stock price volatility based upon an index of the historical volatilities of a group of four publicly
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;traded medical device peer companies. We will continue to apply this process until a sufficient amount of historical information regarding the volatility of our own stock price becomes available. We have estimated the expected term of our employee stock options using the &#x201C;simplified&#x201D; method, whereby the expected life equals the average of the vesting term and the original contractual term of the option. The model and assumptions also attempt to account for changing employee behavior as the stock price changes and capture the observed pattern of increasing rates of exercise as the stock price increases. The use of different values by management in connection with these assumptions in the Black
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;Scholes option pricing model could produce substantially different results.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The assumptions used in the Black
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;Scholes option pricing model are as follows:
</FONT>
</P>
<EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<A NAME="FIS_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE_13"></A>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%;">
<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE;WIDTH: 80.02%;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;">
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="WIDTH:66.70%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-LEFT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-RIGHT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;HEIGHT:1.00PT;PADDING:0PT;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;HEIGHT:1.00PT;OVERFLOW:HIDDEN;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:1PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In July 2014, we granted stock options to purchase an aggregate of 1.2&nbsp;million shares of common stock, which options contain a performance condition such that they only become exercisable in the event that our common stock is listed on a national securities exchange within one year from the date of grant. In accordance with authoritative guidance, we did not record any compensation expense associated with the grants until the performance condition was satisfied in the three month period ended June&nbsp;30, 2015. Upon the completion of the IPO on June&nbsp;30, 2015, we immediately recognized cumulative compensation cost of $3.8&nbsp;million for the grants as if the method had been applied since the date of grant using the required graded accelerated attribution method, and we will record compensation expense over the remainder of the four
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;year vesting period using this method. Stock options granted subsequent to July 2014 do not contain a performance condition.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	85
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage89"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 30PT;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#GKOS-20151231X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#2E74B5;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>
