</EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Recent accounting pronouncements
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In April 2014, the Financial Accounting Standards Board (FASB) issued an accounting standards update
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	(ASU)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	that raises the threshold for disposals to qualify as discontinued operations and allows companies to have significant continuing involvement with and continuing cash flows from or to the discontinued operation. It also requires additional disclosures for discontinued operations and new disclosures for individually material disposal transactions that do not meet the definition of a discontinued operation. This guidance
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	effective for fiscal years beginning after December&nbsp;15, 2014, which was the Company&#x2019;s fiscal year 2015, with early adoption permitted.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	doption of the guidance
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	did not
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	have a material impact on the Company&#x2019;s consolidated financial statements.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In May 2014, the FASB issued guidance codified in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Accounting Standard Codification (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ASC
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	606,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Revenue Recognition&#x2014;Revenue from Contracts with Customers
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, which amends the guidance in former ASC 605,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Revenue Recognition
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, which provides a single comprehensive model for entities to use in accounting for revenue arising from contracts with customers and will supersede most current revenue recognition guidance. This ASU is based on the principle that revenue is recognized to depict the transfer of goods or services to customers in an amount that reflects the consideration to which the entity expects to be entitled in exchange for those goods or services. The ASU also requires additional disclosure about the nature, amount, timing and uncertainty of revenue and cash flows arising from customer contracts, including significant judgments and changes in judgments and assets recognized from costs incurred to obtain or fulfill a contract. In July 2015, the FASB deferred the effective date for annual reporting periods beginning after December&nbsp;15, 2017 (including interim periods within those periods). Early adoption is permitted to the original effective date of December&nbsp;15, 2016 (including interim periods within those periods). The Company is currently evaluating the impact of the provisions of ASC 606 on its
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	consolidated
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	financial statements.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In June 2014, the FASB issued an
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ASU
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	that requires a performance target that affects vesting of a share
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;based payment award and that could be achieved after the requisite service period to be treated as a performance condition. As such, the performance target should not be reflected in estimating the grant date fair value of the award. Compensation cost should
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	101
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<HR ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE='BACKGROUND-COLOR:#000000; BORDER-WIDTH:0; COLOR:#000000; HEIGHT:2PT; LINEHEIGHT:0; WIDTH:100%;'>
</HR>
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage105"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 30PT;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#GKOS-20151231X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#2E74B5;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	be recognized over the required service period if it is probable that the performance target will be achieved. This guidance will be effective for fiscal years beginning after December&nbsp;15, 2015, which will be the Company&#x2019;s fiscal year 2016, with early adoption permitted. The Company does not expect the adoption of the guidance to have material impact on the Company&#x2019;s consolidated financial statements.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In August 2014, the FASB issued ASU No.&nbsp;2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;15,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Disclosure of Uncertainties about an Entity&#x2019;s Ability to Continue as a Going Concern
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. This ASU introduces an explicit requirement for management to assess if there is substantial doubt about an entity&#x2019;s ability to continue as a going concern, and to provide related footnote disclosures in certain circumstances. In connection with each annual and interim period, management must assess if there is substantial doubt about an entity&#x2019;s ability to continue as a going concern within one year after the issuance date. Disclosures are required if conditions give rise to substantial doubt. ASU 2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;15 is effective for all entities in the first annual period ending after December&nbsp;15, 2016. The Company is currently assessing the potential effects of this ASU on the consolidated financial statements.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In February 2015, the FASB issued Accounting Standards Update (ASU) 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;02,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Amendments to the Consolidation Analysis
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, which eliminates the deferral of FAS&nbsp;167, which allows reporting entities with interests in certain investment funds to follow the consolidation guidance in FIN&nbsp;46(R), and make other changes to both the variable interest model and the voting model. The ASU is effective for annual periods beginning after December&nbsp;15, 2015 and interim periods therein, with early adoption permitted. During 2015, the Company early adopted the provisions of the ASU effective January&nbsp;1, 2015. Based on the asset purchase transaction with DOSE on June&nbsp;30, 2015 and the Company&#x2019;s evaluation of the modified relationship with DOSE, management determined that after the transaction DOSE is no longer a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	variable interest entity (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	VIE
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	requiring consolidation (See Note&nbsp;1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In July 2015, the FASB issued ASU 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;11, Inventory (Topic 330),
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Simplifying the Measurement of Inventory
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, which changes the measurement principle for inventory from the lower of cost or market to the lower of cost and net realizable value. ASU 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;11 defines net realizable value as estimated selling prices in the ordinary course of business, less reasonably predictable costs of completion, disposal, and transportation. The new guidance must be applied on a prospective basis and is effective for fiscal years beginning after December&nbsp;15, 2015, and interim periods within those years, with early adoption permitted. The Company does not believe the implementation of this standard will have a material impact on its
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	consolidated
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	financial statements.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In November 2015, the FASB issued guidance on balance sheet classification of deferred taxes. Current GAAP requires an entity to separate deferred income tax liabilities and assets into current and noncurrent amounts in a classified statement of financial position. To simplify the presentation of deferred income taxes, the new guidance requires that deferred tax liabilities and assets be classified as noncurrent in a classified statement of financial position. The current requirement that deferred tax liabilities and assets of a tax-paying component of an entity be offset and presented as a single amount is not affected by this new guidance. The new guidance is effective for fiscal years beginning after December 15, 2016, and interim periods within those annual periods. Earlier application is permitted for all entities as of the beginning of an interim or annual reporting period. For the year ended December 31, 2015, the Company has elected to early adopt this update and will present all its deferred tax assets and liabilities as non-current for the period ended December 31, 2015. The Company has applied the Standard on a prospective basis. Therefore, the classifications of deferred tax assets and liabilities in periods prior to the period ended December 31, 2015 have not been changed from the original presentation.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In February 2016, the FASB issued ASU No. 2016-02,&nbsp;Leases
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	(Topic 842). The ASU requires management to recognize lease assets and lease liabilities by lessees for all operating leases. The ASU is effective for periods ending on December 15, 2018 and interim periods therein on a modified retrospective basis. The Company is currently evaluating the impact this guidance will have on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	its consolidated
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	financial statements.
</FONT>
</P>

</FONT>
</P>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	4.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 28.8PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	Fair value measurements
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Fair value is an exit price, representing the amount that would be received to sell an asset or paid to transfer a liability in an orderly transaction between market participants. As such, fair value is a market
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;based measurement that should be determined based on assumptions that market participants would use in pricing an asset or liability.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>

	104

<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 5PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Money market funds are highly liquid investments and are actively traded. The pricing information on these investment instruments is readily available and can be independently validated as of the measurement date. This approach results in the classification of these securities as Level 1 of the fair value hierarchy.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 5PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	U.S. government agency bonds, commercial paper, corporate notes and asset-backed securities are measured at fair value using Level 2 inputs. The Company reviews trading activity and pricing for these investments as of each measurement date. When sufficient quoted pricing for identical securities is not available, the Company uses market pricing and other observable market inputs for similar securities obtained from third party data providers. These inputs represent quoted prices for similar assets in active markets or these inputs have been derived from observable market data. This approach results in the classification of these securities as Level 2 of the fair value hierarchy.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 5PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The stock warrant liabilit
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	y
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	is
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	recorded at fair value using the Black Scholes option pricing model, which requires inputs such as the expected term of the warrant, volatility and risk free interest rate. These inputs are subjective and generally require significant analysis and judgment to develop, and are therefore considered Level 3 inputs.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 5PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	There were no transfers between levels within the fair value hierarchy during the periods presented.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 5PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	105
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 30PT;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 5PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In con
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	junction with the Company&#x2019;s February 2015 Amended and Restated Revolving Credit and Term Loan Agreement as more fully described in Note&nbsp;6, the Company issued warrants to the lenders to purchase 11,298 shares of common stock at an exercise price of $8.85 per share. Warrants to purchase 5,649 shares of common stock were exercised by the lenders in September 2015. For the year ended December 31, 2015, the Company recorded other expense of $0.2&nbsp;million related to changes in the fair value of the warrants. The fair value of the warrants as of the issuance date was estimated to be $53,000 using an option pricing framework considering multiple exit scenarios and the probability of a down
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;round financing. The following assumptions were deemed by the Company to be significant unobservable inputs: risk
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;free interest rate of 1.9%; dividend yield of 0.0%; expected volatility of 70.0%; and an expected life of 7&nbsp;years. The fair value of the warrants to purchase the remaining 5,649 shares of common stock as of December 31, 2015 was estimated to be $0.1 million using the Black
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;Scholes valuation model with the following assumptions deemed by the Company to be significant unobservable inputs: risk
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;free interest rate of 1.9%; dividend yield of 0.0%; expected volatility of 54.8%; and an expected life of 6.2&nbsp;years. If the value of the underlying shares were to decrease by 10%, the fair value of the warrants would decrease by approximately the same amount.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 5PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In conjunction with loans to the Company in 2010 from certain holders of the Company&#x2019;s then
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;outstanding preferred stock, which shares were subsequently converted into preferred stock in 2011, the Company issued warrants to such holders to purchase 156,860 shares of Series&nbsp;D convertible preferred stock at $7.65 per share. Warrants to purchase 29,334 shares were exercised in 2014. Warrants to purchase 127,526 shares were exercised in 2015; 49,410 warrant shares were exercised with cash payment and 78,116 warrant shares were net exercised into 44,914 shares of common stock immediately prior to the IPO at the IPO price per share of $18.00 per share. For the years ended December&nbsp;31, 2015, 2014 and 2013, the Company recorded other income of approximately $0.9&nbsp;million, $5,000 and $0.3 million, respectively, related to changes in the fair value of the warrants.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

<TD VALIGN="BOTTOM" STYLE="WIDTH:81.10%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-LEFT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-RIGHT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;PADDING:0PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Change in the fair value of stock warrants
</FONT>

	5.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 28.8PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	Convertible notes payable
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In August and October 2012, the Company entered into convertible note agreements with certain holders of its preferred stock to borrow an aggregate of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$10.5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million. The convertible notes included the following terms and conditions: (1)&nbsp;interest rate of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	7.0%;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	(2)&nbsp;principal and interest due upon the earlier of a change in control event or demand at any time after January&nbsp;31, 2013; and (3)&nbsp;automatic conversion of principal and accrued interest into shares of preferred stock at a conversion price equal to the purchase price per share of the equity security issued and sold in the next preferred stock financing. Amounts borrowed under the convertible notes were unsecured. In January 2013, the principal amount
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of the convertible notes and all accrued interest were converted into shares of Series&nbsp;F convertible preferred stock pursuant to the terms of the convertible note agreements.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 36PT;TEXT-INDENT: -36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	6.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 28.8PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	Long
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&#8209;term debt
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:8PT 0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Notes payable in connection with GMP Vision Solutions
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	January 2007, the Company entered into an agreement (the Original GMP Agreement) with GMP Vision Solutions,&nbsp;Inc. (GMP) to acquire certain in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;process research and development. In connection with the Original GMP Agreement, the Company was obligated to make periodic royalty payments equal to a single
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;digit percentage of revenues received for royalty
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;bearing products and periodic royalty payments at a higher royalty rate applied to all amounts received in connection with the grant of licenses or sublicenses of the related intellectual property. No related royalty expense was recorded in cost of sales in the years ended December&nbsp;31, 2015, 2014 and 2013.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In December 2012, the Company entered into an agreement with GMP in which it paid GMP
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$1.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million for a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	90
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;day option to buy out all remaining royalties payable to GMP. In April 2013, the option expired unexercised, and as provided in the agreement, the $1.0&nbsp;million payment satisfied the Company&#x2019;s obligation to pay the first $1.0&nbsp;million in royalties earned beginning on January&nbsp;1, 2013. The $1.0&nbsp;million payment was recorded in cost of sales in the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2012.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In November 2013, the Company entered into an amended agreement with GMP in which remaining royalties payable to GMP (the Buyout Agreement) were canceled in exchange for the issuance of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$17.5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million in promissory notes payable to GMP and a party related to GMP (together, the GMP Note Parties). The GMP notes are collateralized by all of the Company&#x2019;s assets, excluding intellectual property. However, in connection with the Buyout Agreement, the GMP Note Parties entered into agreements with the Company&#x2019;s primary bank pursuant to which any collateralized interests, liens, rights of payment or ability to initiate any enforcement actions in the event of an event of default were subordinate to the rights of the Company&#x2019;s primary bank under the Credit Agreement (and subsequently, the Amended Credit Agreement) which was paid off in full on July&nbsp;31, 2015 (see Note 6).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Buyout Agreement also calls for a payment of up to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$2.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million in the event of a sale of the Company meeting certain criteria. The promissory notes carry an interest rate of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	per annum and required monthly interest only payments from November&nbsp;30, 2013 through December&nbsp;31, 2014 of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$72,900
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, followed by
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	24
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	equal monthly principal and interest payments of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$767,700
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, which began on January&nbsp;31, 2015, and end on December&nbsp;31, 2016.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company concluded that the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$17.5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million transaction represented the purchase of an intangible asset. The Company estimated a useful life of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	five
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	years over which the intangible asset will be amortized to cost of sales in the accompanying statements of operations, which amortization period was determined after consideration of the projected outgoing royalty payment stream had the Buyout Agreement not occurred, and the remaining life of the patents obtained in the Original GMP Agreement. After determining that the pattern of future cash flows assoc
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	iated with this intangible asset could not be reliably estimated with a high level of precision, the Company concluded that the intangible asset will be amortized on a straight
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;line basis over the estimated useful life.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Bank loan facility
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In June 2013, the Company entered into a Loan and Security Agreement (the Credit Agreement) with the Company&#x2019;s primary bank, under which the bank agreed to extend to the Company a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	line of credit
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in the maximum principal amount of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$6.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million. Advances under the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	line of credit
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	were limited to the lesser of (i)&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$6.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million or (ii)&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	77%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of the sum of cash, cash equivalents and eligible domestic accounts receivable. The entire unpaid principal amount plus any accrued but unpaid interest were to become due and payable in full on June&nbsp;5, 2015. Obligations under the Credit Agreement bore interest on the outstanding daily balance thereof at the bank&#x2019;s prime rate plus
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	0.5%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;(
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	3.75%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	at December&nbsp;31, 2014). Amounts owed were secured by a first priority security interest in all of the Company&#x2019;s assets, excluding intellectual property. The Credit Agreement included certain reporting and financial covenants which, if not met, could have constituted an event of default under the Credit Agreement. As of December&nbsp;31, 2015 and 2014, the balance outstanding on the line of credit was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$1.9
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million, respectively. In February 2015, the Agreement was amended and restated, at which time the balance outstanding on the line of credit was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$2.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">

<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

	&nbsp;

<A NAME="eolPage111"></A>

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 30PT;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#GKOS-20151231X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#2E74B5;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>

</DIV>

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In February 2015, the Company and its primary bank executed an Amended and Restated Revolving Credit and Term Loan Agreement (the Amended Credit Agreement) which provided for a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$5.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million senior secured term loan, a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$5.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million senior secured draw
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;to term loan and an
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$8.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million senior secured revolving credit facility. Amounts owed under the Amended Credit Agreement were secured by a first priority security interest in all of the Company&#x2019;s assets, excluding intellectual property. The Amended Credit Agreement included certain reporting and financial covenants which, if not met, could have constituted an event of default under the Amended Credit Agreement.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	On the closing date, the Company received
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$5.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million cash under the senior secured term loan and immediately paid off the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$2.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million balance outstanding on the line of credit under the Credit Agreement. The Company incurred loan origination fees of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$41,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	which was recorded as a loan discount, and debt issuance costs of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$0.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million which was recorded as a deferred asset. The term loan required quarterly principal payments of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$0.4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million over a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;year period beginning May&nbsp;1, 2016. The senior secured draw
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;to term loan was available through February&nbsp;23, 2016 for advances up to an aggregate of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$5.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million, and it required quarterly principal payments equal to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	1/12
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of the aggregate principal amount over a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;year period beginning May&nbsp;1, 2016. As of July&nbsp;31, 2015, the Company had drawn
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$2.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million under the draw
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;to term loan. The senior secured term loan and draw
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;to term loan would have matured and would have been required to be fully paid by February&nbsp;23, 2019. Advances under the revolving line of credit were limited to the lesser of (i)&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$8.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million or (ii)&nbsp;a calculated borrowing base consisting of (a)&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	80%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of eligible accounts receivable plus (b)&nbsp;the lesser of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	30%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of eligible inventory or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$1.5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million. The entire unpaid principal amount plus any accrued but unpaid interest under the revolving line of credit were due to become payable in full on February&nbsp;23, 2017. The Company was permitted to make voluntary prepayments of the term and draw
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;to term loans without prepayment penalty. On July&nbsp;31, 2015, the Company paid off in full all amounts outstanding under the Amended Credit Agreement with the payment of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$7.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million in principal plus all interest and fees payable through the payoff date, and recorded a loss on extinguishment of debt in the amount of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$0.2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million. Accordingly, this facility was terminated and is no longer outstanding and available to the Company.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Outstanding balances under the senior secured term loan and senior secured draw
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;to term loan bore interest on the outstanding daily balance at an annual percentage rate equal to the bank&#x2019;s prime rate plus
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. At the Company&#x2019;s option all or a portion of the amounts owed under any of the senior secured term loan and draw
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;to term loan may have been converted into Eurodollar
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;based advances at an annual percentage rate equal to LIBOR plus
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	3%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. Outstanding balances under the revolving credit facility bore interest on the outstanding daily balance thereof at an annual percentage rate equal to the bank&#x2019;s prime rate plus
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	1.75%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. At the Company&#x2019;s option all or a portion of the amounts owed under the revolving credit facility may have been converted into Eurodollar
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;based advances at an annual percentage rate equal to LIBOR plus
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2.75%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In connection with the execution of the Amended Credit Agreement, the Company issued warrants to the lenders to purchase an aggregate of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	11,298
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	shares of common stock at an exercise price of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$8.85
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	per share as more fully described in Note&nbsp;4. Warrants to purchase
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5,649
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	shares of common stock were exercised by the lenders in September 2015.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company accounted for the debt discount and deferred asset utilizing the effective interest method. Amortization of debt discount and the deferred asset to interest expense amounted to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$15,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	for the year ended December 31, 2015.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

	The Company&#x2019;s debt balances, including current portions, were as follows (in thousands):

	In 2015, the Company entered into agreements with two international distributors pursuant to which their distribution rights with the Company were terminated effective as of December 31, 2015. <DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 30PT;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 12PT 36PT;TEXT-INDENT: -36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	8.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 30PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Stockholders&#x2019; equity
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 10.8PT;TEXT-INDENT: -10.8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Convertible preferred stock
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	On June&nbsp;30, 2015, in connection with the closing of the Company&#x2019;s IPO, all shares of convertible preferred stock automatically converted into common stock at a conversion ratio of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	one
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;one.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Until the conversion of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Company&#x2019;s convertible preferred stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	into common stock in conjunction with the IPO, it was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	classified as temporary equity in the accompanying consolidated balance sheets in accordance with authoritative guidance. The preferred stock was not redeemable; however, upon certain change in control events that are outside of the Company&#x2019;s control, including liquidation, sale or transfer of control of the Company, holders of the convertible preferred stock had the right to receive their liquidation preference under the terms of the Company&#x2019;s pre
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;IPO certificate of incorporation. Accordingly, the Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	did not recognize
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	any accretion of the value of the convertible preferred stock.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In January 2013, the Company issued
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	3.4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million shares of Series&nbsp;F convertible preferred stock (Series&nbsp;F) for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$30.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million, or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$8.85
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	per share. Cash of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$19.2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million was paid for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2.2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million Series&nbsp;F shares and a total of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$10.8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million in principal and accrued interest due under convertible notes was converted into
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	1.2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million Series&nbsp;F shares.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The relative rights, terms, privileges, and restrictions that were granted to or imposed upon preferred stockholders are described below:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 25.2PT;TEXT-INDENT: -10.8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Dividends
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The holders of Series&nbsp;A, B, C, D, E and F convertible preferred stock were entitled to receive annual noncumulative dividends of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$0.20
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$0.432
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$0.56
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$0.612
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$0.674
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$0.708
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	per share, respectively, when and if declared by the Board of Directors, prior and in preference to shareholders of common stock.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	N
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	o
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	dividends
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	were ever
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	declared
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	on the convertible preferred stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 25.2PT;TEXT-INDENT: -10.8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Liquidation preference
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In the event of a liquidation of the Company, holders of Series&nbsp;A, B, C, D, E and F preferred stock were entitled to a liquidation preference of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$2.50
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$5.40
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$7.00
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$7.65
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$8.43
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$8.85
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	per share, as adjusted for any stock dividends, combinations, or splits with respect to such shares, respectively, and any declared but unpaid dividends prior and in preference to any distribution of the assets of the corporation. The remaining assets of the Company were to have been distributed on a pro rata basis to the holders of the common stock.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 25.2PT;TEXT-INDENT: -10.8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Conversion rights
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Each share of Series&nbsp;A, B, C, D, E and F preferred stock was convertible at the option of the holder, at any time after the date of issuance, into common stock at the initial conversion rate of one
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;one. The conversion rate was subject to adjustment for antidilution provisions as defined. The Series&nbsp;A, B, C, D, E and F preferred stock was automatically convertible into common shares upon the earlier of: (a)&nbsp;the day immediately preceding the closing of an underwritten public offering in which the Company receives
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$50.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million or more in gross proceeds or (b)&nbsp;the receipt of consent of the holders of at least
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	67%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of the then outstanding shares of preferred stock, voting together as a single class. On June&nbsp;30, 2015, in connection with the closing of the Company&#x2019;s IPO, all shares of convertible preferred stock automatically converted into common stock at the conversion ratio of one
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;one.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 25.2PT;TEXT-INDENT: -10.8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Voting rights
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Each share of Series&nbsp;A, B, C, D, E and F preferred stock had voting rights equal to an equivalent number of shares of common stock into which it was convertible. The preferred stockholders were entitled to vote as a separate class under specific circumstances.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">

<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 30PT;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	As long as at least
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	1.4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million shares of preferred stock remained outstanding, the Company was required to obtain approval from at least
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	67%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of the holders of preferred stock in order to, among other things, alter the certificate of incorporation as related to preferred stock, change the authorized number of shares of preferred stock, acquire a business, or effect a merger, consolidation or sale of assets where the existing stockholders retain less than
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	51%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of the voting stock of the surviving entity.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In addition to any other vote required by law or the Company&#x2019;s certificate of incorporation, (a)&nbsp;as long as
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	0.4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million shares of Series&nbsp;E preferred stock were outstanding, the Company was required to obtain the approval of the holders of a majority of the Series&nbsp;E preferred stock in order to, among other things, alter the certificate of incorporation as it relates to the Series&nbsp;E preferred stock, change the authorized number of shares of Series&nbsp;E preferred stock, sell or license the Company&#x2019;s assets or effect a merger or consolidation where the existing stockholders retain less than
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	51%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of the voting power of the surviving corporation and the stock price is less than
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$15.30
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	per share, or take any action that would alter or waive certain liquidation rights of the Series&nbsp;E preferred stock and (b)&nbsp;as long as
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	0.2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million shares of Series&nbsp;F preferred stock were outstanding, the Company was required to obtain the approval of the holders of at least
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	60%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of the Series&nbsp;F preferred stock in order to, among other things, alter the certificate of incorporation as it relates to the Series&nbsp;F preferred stock, change the authorized number of shares of Series&nbsp;E preferred stock, sell or license the Company&#x2019;s assets or effect a merger or consolidation where the existing stockholders retain less than
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	51%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of the voting power of the surviving corporation and the stock price is less than
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$15.30
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	per share, or take any action that would alter or waive certain liquidation rights of the Series&nbsp;F preferred stock.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 25.2PT;TEXT-INDENT: -10.8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Preferred stock
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company is authorized to issue
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	5.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million shares of its preferred stock.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	No
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	shares of preferred stock have been issued
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	since it was authorized in June 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 25.2PT;TEXT-INDENT: -10.8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Common stock
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Prior to the completion of the Company&#x2019;s IPO in June 2015, all common stock issued resulted from the founding of the Company and the exercises of stock options. On June 30, 2015, the Company completed its IPO, selling
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	6.9
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million newly issued shares of common stock at a price of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$18.00
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	per share. Immediately prior to the closing of the IPO, all unexercised warrants to purchase shares of Series D convertible preferred stock were net exercised at the IPO price per share, and then all outstanding shares of convertible preferred stock automatically converted into approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	21.7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million shares of common stock.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In 2013, the Company repurchased at fair market value and placed into treasury
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	28,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	shares of its common stock that had been acquired in connection with the exercise of a stock option.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 25.2PT;TEXT-INDENT: -10.8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	-
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	based compensation
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company has
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	four
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;based compensation plans (collectively, the Stock Plans)&#x2014;the 2001 Stock Option Plan (the 2001 Stock Plan), the 2011 Stock Plan, the 2015 Omnibus Incentive Compensation Plan (the 2015 Stock Plan) and the 2015 Employee Stock Purchase Plan (the ESPP). The purpose of these plans is to provide incentives to employees, directors and nonemployee consultants. The Company will no longer grant any awards under the 2001 Stock Plan and the 2011 Stock Plan. The maximum term of any stock options granted under the Stock Plans is
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	10
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;years. The options generally vest
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	25%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	on the first anniversary of the original vesting date, with the balance vesting monthly or annually over the remaining
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	years. Stock options are granted at exercise prices at least equal to the fair value of the underlying stock at the date of the grant. The Company reserved an aggregate of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	4.5
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million shares of common stock for issuance under the 2015 Stock Plan, and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	450,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	shares of common stock for issuance under the ESPP that permits eligible employees to purchase shares of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	t
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	he Company&#x2019;s common stock, using contributions via payroll deduction of up to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	15%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ir
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	earnings
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	at a price per share equal to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	85%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of the lower of the stock&#x2019;s fair market value on the offering date or purchase date. The ESPP is intended to qualify as an &#x201C;employee stock purchase plan&#x201D; under Section&nbsp;423 of the Internal Revenue Code.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Stock options granted pursuant to the 2001 Stock Plan and 2011 Stock Plan generally permit optionees to elect to exercise unvested options in exchange for restricted common stock. All unvested shares issued upon the early exercise of stock options, so long as they remain unvested, are subject to the Company&#x2019;s right of repurchase at the optionee&#x2019;s original exercise price for a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	90
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;day
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	period beginning on the date that an optionee&#x2019;s service with the Company voluntarily or involuntarily terminates. Consistent with authoritative guidance, early exercises are not considered exercises for accounting purposes. Cash received for the exercise of unvested options is recorded as a liability, which liability is released to equity at each reporting date as the shares vest. During the years ended December&nbsp;31, 2015, 2014 and 2013, there were option exercises for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	337
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	55,908
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	unvested shares, respectively. As of December&nbsp;31, 2015 and 2014,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	16,682
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	38,678
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	shares, respectively, remained subject to a repurchase right
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	by the Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. As of December&nbsp;31, 2015 and 2014, the related liability, which is included in other accrued liabilities in the accompanying consolidated balance sheets, was approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$67,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$153,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, respectively.
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The weighted average estimated grant date fair value per share of stock options granted during the years ended December&nbsp;31, 2015, 2014 and 2013 was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$9.77
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$4.08
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$2.53
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, respectively. At December&nbsp;31, 2015, the total unamortized stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;based compensation expense of approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$11.7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million is to be recognized over the stock options&#x2019; remaining vesting terms of approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	4.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;years (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	3.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;years on a weighted average basis).
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The total fair value of stock options that vested during the years ended December 31, 2015 and 2014 was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$5.2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$1.8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million, respectively.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In July 2014, the Company granted stock options to purchase an aggregate of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	1.2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million shares of common stock, which options contain a performance condition such that they would only become exercisable in the event that the Company&#x2019;s common stock was listed on a national securities exchange within one year from the date of grant. In accordance with authoritative guidance, the Company did not record any compensation expense associated with the grants until the performance condition was satisfied on June&nbsp;30, 2015. As of December&nbsp;31, 2014 and June&nbsp;30, 2015, the total unamortized share
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;based compensation expense for these grants was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$4.9
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million. Upon the completion of the IPO on June&nbsp;30, 2015, the Company immediately recognized cumulative compensation cost of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$3.8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million for the grants as if the method had been applied since the date of grant using the required graded accelerated attribution method, and the Company will record compensation expense over the remainder of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	four
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;year vesting period using this method. Stock options granted subsequent to July 2014 do not contain a performance condition.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company uses the Black
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;Scholes option
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;pricing model to estimate the fair value of stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;based awards on the date of grant. The determination of fair value using the Black
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;Scholes option
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;pricing model is affected by the estimated fair market value per share of the Company&#x2019;s common stock as well as assumptions regarding a number of highly complex and subjective variables, including expected stock price volatility, risk
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;free interest rate, expected dividends and expected option life and generally requires significant management judgment to determine.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Risk
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#8209;free interest rate.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;The risk
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;free interest rate is equal to the U.S. Treasury Note interest rate for the comparable term for the expected option life as of the valuation date. If the expected option life is between the U.S. Treasury Note rates of two published terms, then the risk
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;free interest rate is based on the straight
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;line interpolation between the U.S. Treasury Note rates of the two published terms as of the valuation date.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Expected dividend yield.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;The expected dividend yield is based on the Company&#x2019;s history and expectation of dividend payouts. The Company has never declared or paid any cash dividends and does not presently plan to pay cash dividends in the foreseeable future.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Expected volatility.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;The Company only recently began to have publicly traded equity and has a limited operating history and a lack of Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;specific historical and implied volatility data, and therefore has estimated its stock price volatility based upon an index of the historical volatilities of a group of comparable publicly
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;traded medical device peer companies. The historical volatility data was computed using the historical daily closing prices for the selected peer companies&#x2019; shares during the equivalent period of the calculated expected term of the Company&#x2019;s share
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;based awards. The Company will continue to apply this process until a sufficient amount of historical information regarding the volatility of its own stock price becomes available.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Expected term.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;The Company has concluded that its stock option exercise history does not provide a reasonable basis upon which to estimate expected term, and therefore it uses the simplified method for estimating the expected term of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	113
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 30PT;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#GKOS-20151231X10K_HTM_TOC">

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	stock option grants. Under this approach, the weighted
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;average expected term is presumed to be the average of the vesting term and the contractual term of the option.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Fair value of common stock.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;Historically, and until the June&nbsp;30, 2015 completion of the Company&#x2019;s IPO, the fair value of the shares of common stock underlying the stock options has been the responsibility of and determined by the Company&#x2019;s Board of Directors. Because there had been no public market for the Company&#x2019;s common stock, the Board of Directors determined the fair value of common stock at the time of grant of the option by considering a number of objective and subjective factors including independent third
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;party valuations of the Company&#x2019;s common stock, sales prices of convertible preferred stock to unrelated third parties, operating and financial performance, the lack of liquidity of capital stock and general and industry specific economic outlook, among other factors. Subsequent to the date of the Company&#x2019;s IPO in June 2015, the Company has used the daily market prices in the determination of the fair value of its common stock.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 10.8PT;TEXT-INDENT: -10.8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#8209;based awards to employees
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The weighted
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;average assumptions used to estimate the fair value of options granted to employees were as follows:
</FONT>
</P>
<EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<A NAME="FIS_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE_33"></A>

	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT 9PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Forfeiture rate.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;The Company reduces employee share
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;based compensation expense for estimated forfeitures. Forfeitures are estimated at the time of grant based on historical experience, and revised, if necessary, in subsequent periods if actual forfeitures differ from those estimates.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 9PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The weighted
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;average per share exercise price of options granted to employees during the years ended December&nbsp;31, 2015, 2014 and 2013 was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$17.79
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$7.13
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$4.30
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, respectively.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 9PT 10.8PT;TEXT-INDENT: -10.8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&#8209;based awards to nonemployees
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 9PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The fair values of stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;based awards made to nonemployees are remeasured at the end of the reporting period using the Black
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;Scholes option pricing model. The expected life for each option is determined based on the time remaining until the expiration of the option as of the date of remeasurement. Compensation expense for these share
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;based awards is determined by applying the recalculated fair values to the shares that have vested during a period.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 9PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	891,400
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	shares of common stock at exercise prices ranging from
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$0.25

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$25.91
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	per share. For the years ended December&nbsp;31, 2015, 2014 and 2013, the Company recorded nonemployee stock
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;based compensation expense of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$1.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$0.3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$0.3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million, respectively.

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Based on the weight of available evidence, management has established a valuation allowance for all of the deferred tax assets as it is more likely than not that the deferred tax assets will not be realized.&nbsp;&nbsp;The net change in the valuation allowance was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$9.4
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million in 2015.
</FONT>
</P>

	At December&nbsp;31, 2015, the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	C
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	ompany had approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$118.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$98.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$2.3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million of net operating loss carryforwards for federal, state and foreign purposes, respectively, available to offset future taxable income. The federal and state net operating loss carryforwards begin to expire in 2018 and 2016, respectively.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Japan tax loss of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$0.7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million will expire in 2024 if not sooner utilized. The remaining foreign tax losses effectively do not expire.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	At December&nbsp;31, 2015, the Company had federal and state research and development credit carryforwards of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$4.6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million, respectively, which begin to expire in 2021 for federal purposes and carry over indefinitely for state purposes.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 8PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Utilization of the net operating loss and tax credit carryforwards will be subject to annual limitations under Sections&nbsp;382 and 383 of the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 and similar state provisions due to several ownership changes that have occurred previously or that could occur in the future. These ownership changes will limit the amount of net operating loss and tax credit carryforwards and other deferred tax assets that can be utilized to offset future taxable income and tax. In general, all ownership changes as defined by Section&nbsp;382 result from transactions increasing ownership of certain stockholders in the stock of the Company by more than 50&nbsp;percentage points over a three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;year period. An analysis was performed by the Company which indicated that several ownership changes have occurred in previous years which created annual limitations on the Company&#x2019;s ability to utilize net operating loss and tax credit carryforwards. Such limitations will result in approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$0.2
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million of tax benefits related to net operating loss and tax credit
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>

	As of December 31, 2015,

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	r
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	e would be no impact on the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	effective tax rate if the uncertain tax benefits were recognized
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company&#x2019;s policy is to recognize interest expense and penalties related to income tax matters as a component of income tax expense. There was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	no
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	accrued interest and penalties associated with uncertain tax positions as of December&nbsp;31, 2015 and 2014. It is not anticipated that there will be a significant change in the unrecognized tax benefits over the next 12&nbsp;months.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Due to the Company&#x2019;s net operating loss carryforwards, its federal, state and foreign income tax returns are open to examination by the Internal Revenue Service and state jurisdictions for all years since inception.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 36PT;TEXT-INDENT: -36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 27PT 0PT 0PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Employee benefits
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
