	The Company sponsors a defined contribution plan pursuant to section&nbsp;401(k) of the United States Internal Revenue Code that allows participating employees to contribute up to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	100%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of their salary, to an annual maximum of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$17,500

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in 2014 and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$18,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in 2015 (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$23,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$24,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	in 2014 and 2015, respectively, for employees over the age of 50). The Company may contribute at its discretion. To date, the Company has only made &#x201C;qualified nonelective contributions&#x201D; to maintain compliance with IRS regulations.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	No
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	plan contributions were made by the Company in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2015

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, 2014 and 2013.

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 27PT 0PT 0PT;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

	The Company, from time to time, is involved in legal proceedings or regulatory encounters or other matters in the ordinary course of business that could result in unasserted or asserted claims or litigation. </FONT>

	no
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company leases its main headquarters and manufacturing facility and facilities for its foreign subsidiaries.&nbsp;&nbsp;Certain of the Company&#x2019;s leases contain renewal options, rent escalation clauses, and/or landlord incentives.&nbsp;&nbsp;Rent expense for noncancelable operating leases with scheduled rent increases and/or landlord incentives is recognized on a straight-line basis over the lease term beginning with the lease commencement date, or the date the Company takes control of the leased space, whichever is sooner.&nbsp;&nbsp;The excess of straight-line rent expense over scheduled payment amounts and landlord incentives is recorded as a deferred rent liability.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The current main facility leases in Laguna Hills, California for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	23,915
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	square feet expire on
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	September
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	, 2016.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In June 2015, the Company entered into a sublease for an approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	37,700
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	square foot facility located in San Clemente, California effective September&nbsp;1, 2015,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	five
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;year lease for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	the facility
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	that takes effect January&nbsp;1, 2017 upon expiration of the sublease.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	This facility is intended to become the Company&#x2019;s main headquarters and manufacturing facility.&nbsp;&nbsp;Rent under the direct lease begins on January 1, 2017 at approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$42,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	per month, with rent for the second and third months abated, and the annual rent payments increase beginning on January 1, 2018 at percentages ranging from
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2.5%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	3.5%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;The direct lease agreement contains an option to extend the lease for up to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	two
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	additional
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	-year periods at market rates.&nbsp;&nbsp;The direct lease landlord has agreed to provide the Company with a tenant improvement allowance on January 1, 2017 in the amount of the cost of any leasehold improvements, not to exceed approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$264,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:12PT 0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Purchase commitment
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company is a party to various purchase arrangements related to components used in production and research and development activities. As of December&nbsp;31, 2015, the Company had noncancelable, firm purchase commitments with certain vendors totaling approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	2.6
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million, due within one year. There are no material purchase commitments due beyond one year.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Regents of the University of California
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	On December&nbsp;30, 2014, the Company executed an agreement (the UC Agreement) with the Regents of the University of California (the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	University
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	) to correct inventorship in connection with a group of the Company&#x2019;s U.S. patents (the Patent Rights) and to obtain from the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	University
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	a covenant that it did not and would not claim any right or title to the Patent Rights and will not challenge or assist any others in challenging the Patent Rights. In connection with the Agreement, Glaukos agreed to pay to the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	University
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	the sum of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$2.7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million via
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	five
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	payments during the course of 2015, and, beginning with sales on or after January&nbsp;1, 2015, to pay a low single
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;digit percentage of worldwide net sales of certain current and future products, including the Company&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iStent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	products, with a required minimum annual payment of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$500,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	. This ongoing
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	product
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	payment terminates on the date that the last of the Patent Rights expires, which is currently expected to be in 2022.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In 2015, the Company recorded approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$1.8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million in cost of sales in connection with this product payment obligation.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The $2.7&nbsp;million obligation, net of imputed interest of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$0.1
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million, was accrued as of December&nbsp;31, 2014 and charged to cost of sales in the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2014. Under the terms of the UC Agreement, the payments comprising the $2.7&nbsp;million obligation were due within
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	60
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;days of the IPO, and, accordingly, the Company paid the remaining balance due of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$1.8
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million prior to August&nbsp;29, 2015.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Transcend Medical Litigation Settlement
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	On October 29, 2015, the Company entered into a settlement agreement with Transcend Medical, Inc. (Transcend) to resolve the patent litigation then pending between the companies before the U.S. District Court for the District of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	118
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<HR ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE='BACKGROUND-COLOR:#000000; BORDER-WIDTH:0; COLOR:#000000; HEIGHT:2PT; LINEHEIGHT:0; WIDTH:100%;'>
</HR>
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage122"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 30PT;COLOR:#000000;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<A HREF="#GKOS-20151231X10K_HTM_TOC">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#2E74B5;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Delaware.&nbsp;&nbsp;Under the settlement agreement, the Company granted Transcend a covenant not to sue Transcend for patent infringement in connection with Transcend&#x2019;s CyPass Micro-Stent devices, appliers and delivery systems.&nbsp;&nbsp;In exchange, Transcend granted the Company a covenant not to challenge the validity or enforceability of any Glaukos patent and will make quarterly payments to the Company equal to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	1%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of future net sales of the CyPass Micro-Stent devices until April 8, 2022 or up to a maximum aggregate payment amount of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$6.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	million.&nbsp;&nbsp;In connection with the settlement agreement, the parties filed a joint stipulation of dismissal with prejudice of all of their respective claims against each other in this matter, with each party responsible for its own legal expenses.&nbsp;&nbsp;The court dismissed the matter with prejudice on October 29, 2015 and the need for the trial that was scheduled to begin November 2, 2015 was eliminated.&nbsp;&nbsp;In connection with entering into the settlement agreement, the Company agreed to pay the Regents
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	33%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	of any payments the Company receives from Transcend pursuant to the settlement agreement
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 36PT;TEXT-INDENT: -36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	12.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 27PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Variable interest entity
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	In October 2009, the Company formed a wholly
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;owned subsidiary, DOSE Medical Corporation and in April 2010, the Company distributed all of its shares of common stock of DOSE via a stock dividend to the Company&#x2019;s stockholders of record as of the close of business on March&nbsp;31, 2010. Since its formation, the Company had provided DOSE with a small number of leased employees, management services and space, all of which had been charged to DOSE and pursuant to written agreements between the parties. Additionally, the Company had provided DOSE the cash required to fund its operations that, together with accrued interest and charges for the aforementioned services, the Company had recorded in an intercompany receivable account. Up until the transaction on June&nbsp;30, 2015 described below, the Company had accounted for DOSE as a variable interest entity in which it had a variable interest in all reporting periods since the formation of DOSE. Accordingly, the Company&#x2019;s consolidated financial statements include the accounts of DOSE, with all intercompany balances eliminated and with the deficit balance of DOSE&#x2019;s net assets reflected as noncontrolling interest, up to but excluding June&nbsp;30, 2015.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	On June&nbsp;30, 2015, the Company completed a transaction initially executed in July 2014, the closing of which was contingent upon the successful completion of an IPO. Pursuant to the terms of the asset purchase agreement, the Company acquired from DOSE certain assets, including the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	iDose
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	product line, in exchange for payment of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$15.0
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million in cash and the elimination of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$10.9
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million intercompany receivable owed by DOSE to the Company as of the closing date. In addition to the asset purchase agreement, the parties agreed to an amended and restated patent license agreement and an amended and restated transition services agreement that provides for limited support from the Company to DOSE for a period of up to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	years. Either party can terminate the transition services agreement upon adequate written notice.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Two
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	members of the Company&#x2019;s board of directors currently serve on the board of directors of DOSE.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The Company has reconsidered its relationship with DOSE as a result of the transaction and has determined that the Company is no longer considered to be the primary beneficiary with the power to direct operations and the right to receive benefits/absorb losses of DOSE; therefore, upon the close of the transaction, the Company derecognized DOSE and will no longer consider it a consolidated entity in its financial statements. Accordingly, in the three months ended June&nbsp;30, 2015, the Company recorded a charge to other expense in the amount of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	$25.7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million to reflect the deconsolidation of DOSE&#x2019; non
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#8209;glaucoma related assets and noncontrolling interest.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	The carrying amount and classification of DOSE&#x2019;s assets and liabilities that are included in the accompanying consolidated balance sheets are as follows (in thousands):
</FONT>
</P>

<EFX_CONTROL_AND_PROCEDURES>
<A NAME="FIS_CONTROL_AND_PROCEDURES"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT 54PT;PUNCTUATION-WRAP:HANGING;TEXT-INDENT: -54PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	ITEM 9A.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 30PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	CONTROL
</FONT>
<A NAME="GKOS-20151231X10K_HTM_ITEM9ACONTROLS_947304">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	S AND PROCEDURES
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;PUNCTUATION-WRAP:HANGING;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Evaluation of Disclosure Controls and Procedures
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;PUNCTUATION-WRAP:HANGING;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;COLOR:#231F20;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#231F20;">
	The term &#x201C;disclosure controls and procedures,&#x201D; as defined in Rules 13a-15(e) and 15d-15(e) under the Exchange Act, refers to controls and procedures that are designed to ensure that information required to be disclosed by a company in the reports that it files or submits under the Exchange Act is recorded, processed, summarized and reported within the time periods specified in the SEC&#x2019;s rules and forms. Disclosure controls and procedures include, without limitation, controls and procedures designed to ensure that information required to be disclosed by a company in the reports that it files or submits under the Exchange Act is accumulated and communicated to the company&#x2019;s management, including its principal executive and principal financial officers, or persons performing similar functions, as appropriate to allow timely decisions regarding required disclosure. Our management recognizes that any controls and procedures, no matter how well designed and operated, can provide only reasonable assurance of achieving their objectives and our management necessarily applies its judgment in evaluating the cost-benefit relationship of possible controls and procedures. Our management, with the participation of our chief executive officer and our chief financial officer, evaluated the effectiveness of our disclosure controls and procedures as of the end of the period covered by this report. Based on that evaluation, our chief executive officer and our chief financial officer concluded that our disclosure controls and procedures were effective, at the reasonable assurance level, as of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#231F20;">
	December&nbsp;31, 2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#231F20;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:BOOK ANTIQUA;COLOR:#231F20;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;PUNCTUATION-WRAP:HANGING;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Changes in Internal Control over Financial Reporting
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;PUNCTUATION-WRAP:HANGING;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;COLOR:#231F20;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#231F20;">
	There have been no changes in our internal control over financial reporting
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#231F20;">
	, as such term is defined in Rules&nbsp;13a-15(f) and 15d-15(f) under the Exchange Act,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;COLOR:#231F20;">
	during our fourth fiscal quarter of 2015 that have materially affected, or are reasonably likely to materially affect, our internal control over financial reporting.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-FAMILY:BOOK ANTIQUA;COLOR:#231F20;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Exemption from Management&#x2019;s Report
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	and Auditor Attestation
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	on Internal Control Over Financial
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	This Annual Report on Form 10-K does not include a report of management&#x2019;s assessment regarding internal control over financial reporting or an attestation report of our independent registered public accounting firm due to a transition period established by rules of the SEC for newly public companies
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	and emerging growth companies
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
</EFX_CONTROL_AND_PROCEDURES>

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:10.2941176470588%;MARGIN-RIGHT:10.2941176470588%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">

	We have adopted a written code of business conduct and ethics that applies to our directors, executive officers and employees, including our principal executive officer, principal financial officer, principal accounting officer or controller, or persons performing similar functions. A current copy of the code is posted on the investor section of our website,
</FONT>

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">

</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 1PT 7.2PT;TEXT-INDENT: -7.2PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 8PT;">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:5.88235294117647%;MARGIN-RIGHT:5.88235294117647%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<A NAME="GKOS-20151231EX1023F5A8B_HTM__GOBACK">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Exhibit 10.23
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	THIRD AMENDMENT TO LEASE
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	This Third Amendment to Lease (&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Third Amendment
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;) is dated for reference purposes the 23rd day of November, 2015, and is entered into by and between Laguna Cabot Road Business Park, LP (&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Landlord
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;), and Glaukos Corporation (&#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Tenant
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;), with reference to the following recitals.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	RECITALS
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	A.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	On or about October 1, 2005, Landlord and Tenant entered into a Standard Business Park Lease
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x2014; Multi-Tenant (the &#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Original Lease
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;) for that certain premises of approximately 20,800 square feet in size and commonly known as Suites 103, 104 and 105, 26051 Merit Circle, Laguna Hills, California (the &#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Premises
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;).&nbsp;&nbsp;On or about October 8, 2008, Landlord and Tenant entered into a First Amendment to Lease (the &#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	First Amendment
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;).On or about September 30, 2011, Landlord and Tenant entered into a Second Amendment to Lease (the &#x201C;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Second Amendment
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&#x201D;).&nbsp;&nbsp;The Original Lease as modified by the First and Second Amendment is hereinafter referred to as the &#x201C;Lease&#x201D;,
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	B,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Tenant and Landlord acknowledge and agree that all prior tenant improvements and other work to be performed by Landlord under the Lease have been completed and accepted by Tenant, there are no defaults under the Lease by either Landlord or Tenant, all obligations of Landlord and Tenant accruing prior to the date of this amendment have been performed by Landlord and Tenant and that the Existing Premises are being leased in its &#x201C;as is&#x201D;, &#x201C;where is&#x201D; &#x201C;with all faults&#x201D; condition.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 12PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;TEXT-INDENT:36PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	C.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Landlord and Tenant wish to amend the Lease to extend the term and modify the rent and other terms and conditions as set forth below.

<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-RIGHT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;WIDTH:47.46%;PADDING:0PT;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">

<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:5.88235294117647%;MARGIN-RIGHT:5.88235294117647%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Note:&nbsp;&nbsp;The State of California uses the following terms interchangeably:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	Seller = Landlord = Lessor; Buyer = Tenant = Lessee
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:5.88235294117647%;MARGIN-RIGHT:5.88235294117647%;">
<HR ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE='BACKGROUND-COLOR:#000000; BORDER-WIDTH:0; COLOR:#000000; HEIGHT:2PT; LINEHEIGHT:0; WIDTH:100%;'>
</HR>
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage137"></A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:5.88235294117647%;MARGIN-RIGHT:5.88235294117647%;">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:5.88235294117647%;MARGIN-RIGHT:5.88235294117647%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%;">
<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE;WIDTH: 100.00%;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;">
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="WIDTH:100.00%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-LEFT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-RIGHT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;HEIGHT:1.00PT;PADDING:0PT 6.5PT">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;HEIGHT:1.00PT;OVERFLOW:HIDDEN;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;HEIGHT:1.00PT;OVERFLOW:HIDDEN;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;HEIGHT:1.00PT;OVERFLOW:HIDDEN;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:2PT DOUBLE #000000 ;BORDER-RIGHT:2PT DOUBLE #000000 ;BORDER-LEFT:2PT DOUBLE #000000 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:2PT DOUBLE #000000 ;WIDTH:100.00%;PADDING:0PT 6.5PT">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:6PT 0PT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	Please note that the terms &#x201C;Seller&#x201D; and &#x201C;Buyer&#x201D; are defined by the CA Civil Code to include a lessor and lessee, respectively.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	If you are a Listing Agent - you must deliver the form to the seller/lessor before entering into the listing agreement.&nbsp;&nbsp;If the buyer/lessee is not represented by an agent, you must also deliver the form to it within one business day after receiving an offer from the buyer/lessee.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	If you are the Buyer&#x2019;s Agent - you must deliver the form in the buyer/lessee as soon as the buyer/lessee seeks your services, but in any event before the buyer/lessee signs an offer.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, you must also deliver the form to the seller/lessor before or concurrently with presenting an offer.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	DISCLOSURE REGARDING REAL ESTATE AGENCY RELATIONSHIP
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	When you enter into a discussion with a real estate agent regarding a real estate transaction, you should from the outset understand what type of agency relationship or representation you wish to have with the agent in the transaction.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	SELLER&#x2019;S AGENT
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	A Seller&#x2019;s agent under a listing agreement with the Seller acts as the agent for the Seller only.&nbsp;&nbsp;A Seller&#x2019;s agent or a subagent of that agent has the following affirmative obligations:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	To the Seller
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	:&nbsp;&nbsp;A fiduciary duty of utmost care, integrity, honesty, and loyalty in dealings with the Seller.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	To the Buyer and the Seller
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT 36PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 11.7PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	Diligent exercise of reasonable skill and care in performance of the agent&#x2019;s duties.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT 36PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 11.7PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	A duty of honest end fair dealing and good faith.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT 36PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	(c)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 11.7PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	A duty to disclose all facts known to the agent materially affecting the value or desirability of the property that are not known to, or within the diligent attention and observation of, the parties.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	An agent is not obligated to reveal to either party any confidential information obtained from the other pally that does not involve the affirmative duties set forth above.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:7PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	BUYER&#x2019;S AGENT
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	A selling agent can, with a Buyer&#x2019;s consent, agree to act as agent for the Buyer only.&nbsp;&nbsp;In these situations, the agent is not the Seller&#x2019;s agent, even if by agreement the agent may receive compensation for services rendered, either in full or in part from the Seller.&nbsp;&nbsp;An agent acting only for a Buyer has the following affirmative obligations:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	To the Buyer
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	: A fiduciary duty of utmost care, integrity, honesty, and loyalty in dealings with the Buyer.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	To the Buyer and the Seller
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT 36PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 11.7PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	Diligent exercise of reasonable skill and care in performance of the agent&#x2019;s duties.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT 36PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 11.7PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	A duty of honest and fair dealing and good faith.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT 36PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	(c)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 11.7PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	A duty to disclose all facts known to the agent materially affecting the value or desirability of the property that are not known to, or within the diligent attention and observation of, the parties.&nbsp;&nbsp;An agent is not obligated to reveal to either party any confidential information obtained from the other party that does riot involve the affirmative duties set forth above.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:7PT;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	AGENT REPRESENTING BOTH SELLER AND BUYER
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	A real estate agent, either acting directly or through one or more associate licensees, can legally be the agent of both the Seller and the Buyer in a transaction, but only with the knowledge and consent of both the Seller and the Buyer.&nbsp;&nbsp;In a dual agency situation, the agent has the following affirmative obligations to both the Seller and the Buyer:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT 36PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 11.7PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	A fiduciary duty of utmost care, integrity, honesty and loyalty in the dealings with either the Seller or he Suva-.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT 36PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;PADDING:0PT 11.7PT 0PT 0PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	Other duties to the Seller and the Buyer as stated above in their respective sections.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	In representing both Seller and Buyer, the agent may not, without the express permission of the respective party, disclose to the other party that the Seller will accept a price less than the listing price or that the Buyer will pay a price greeter than the price offered.&nbsp;&nbsp;The above duties of the agent in a real estate transaction do not relieve a Seller or Buyer from the responsibility to protect his or her own interests.&nbsp;&nbsp;You should carefully read all agreements to assure that they adequately express your understanding of the transaction.&nbsp;&nbsp;A real estate agent is a person qualified to advise about real estate.&nbsp;&nbsp;If legal or tax advice is desired, consult a competent professional.&nbsp;&nbsp;Throughout your real property transaction you may receive more than one disclosure form, depending upon the number of agents assisting in the transaction.&nbsp;&nbsp;The law requires each agent with whom you have more than a casual relationship to present you with this disclosure form.&nbsp;&nbsp;You should read its contents each time it is presented to you, considering the relationship between you and the real estate agent in your specific transaction.&nbsp;&nbsp;This disclosure form includes the provisions of Sections 2079.13 to 2079.24, inclusive, of the Civil Code set forth on the reverse hereof.&nbsp;&nbsp;Read it carefully.
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="WIDTH:37.18%;BORDER-TOP:1PT SOLID #000000 ;BORDER-LEFT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-RIGHT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;PADDING:0PT;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	Seller/Lessor Printed Name
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" STYLE="WIDTH:10.00%;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-LEFT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-RIGHT:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;PADDING:0PT;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:6PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:5.88235294117647%;MARGIN-RIGHT:5.88235294117647%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:5.88235294117647%;MARGIN-RIGHT:5.88235294117647%;">
<HR ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE='BACKGROUND-COLOR:#000000; BORDER-WIDTH:0; COLOR:#000000; HEIGHT:2PT; LINEHEIGHT:0; WIDTH:100%;'>
</HR>
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage138"></A>
</DIV>
</EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:5.88235294117647%;MARGIN-RIGHT:5.88235294117647%;">
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:5.88235294117647%;MARGIN-RIGHT:5.88235294117647%;">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:6PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	2079.13.&nbsp;&nbsp;As used in Sections 2079.14 in 2079.24, inclusive, the following terms have the following meanings:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 18PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&#x201C;Agent&#x201D; means a person acting under provisions of Title 9 (commencing with Section 2295) in a real property transaction, and includes a person who is licensed as a real estate broker under Chapter 3 (commencing with Section 10130) of Part 1 of Division 4 of the Business and Professions Code, and under whose license a listing is executed or an offer to purchase is Obtained.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 18PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&#x201C;Associate licensee&#x201D; means a person who is licensed as a real estate broker or salesperson under Chapter 3 (commencing with Section 10130) of Part 1 of Division 4 of the Business and Professions Code and who is either licensed under a broker or has entered into a written contract with a broker to act as the broker&#x2019;s agent in connection with acts requiring a real estate license and to function under the broker&#x2019;s supervision in the capacity of an associate licensee.&nbsp;&nbsp;The agent in the real property transaction bears responsibility for his or her associate licensees who perform as agents of the agent.&nbsp;&nbsp;When an associate licensee owes a duty to any principal, or to any buyer or seller who is not a principal, in a real property transaction, that duty is equivalent to the duty owed to that party by the broker for whom the associate licensee functions.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 18PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	(c)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&#x201C;Buyer&#x201D; means a transferee in a real property transaction, and includes a person who executes an offer to purchase real property from a seller through an agent, or who seeks the services of an agent in more than a casual, transitory, or preliminary manner, with the object of entering into a real property transaction.&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x201C;Buyer&#x201D; includes vendee or lessee.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 18PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	(d)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&#x201C;Dual agent&#x201D; means an agent acting, either directly or through an associate licensee, as agent for both the seller and the buyer in a real property transaction.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 18PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	(e)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&#x201C;Listing agreement&#x201D; means a contract between an owner of real property and an agent, by which the agent has been authorized to sell the real property or to find or obtain a buyer.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 18PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	(f)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&#x201C;Listing agent&#x201D; meets a person who has obtained a listing of real property to act as an agent for compensation.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 18PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	(g)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&#x201C;Listing price&#x201D; is the amount expressed in dollars specified in the listing for which the seller is willing to sell the real property through the listing agent.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 18PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	(h)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&#x201C;Offering price&#x201D; is the amount expressed in dollars specified in an offer to purchase for which the buyer is willing to buy the real property.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 18PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	(i)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&#x201C;Offer to purchase&#x201D; means a written contract executed by a buyer acting through a selling agent which becomes the contract for the sale of the real property upon acceptance by the seller.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 18PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	(j)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&#x201C;Real property&#x201D; means any estate specified by subdivision (1) or (2) of Section 761 in property which constitutes or is improved with one to four dwelling units, any leasehold in this type of property exceeding one year&#x2019;s duration, and mobile homes, when offered for sale or sold through an agent pursuant to the authority contained in Section 10131.6 of the Business and Professions Code.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 18PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	(k)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&#x201C;Real property transaction&#x201D; means in transaction for the sale of real property in which an agent is employed by one or more of the principals to act in that transaction, and includes a listing or an offer to purchase.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 18PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	(l)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&#x201C;Sell,&#x201D; &#x201C;sale,&#x201D; or &#x201C;sold&#x2019; refers to a transaction for the transfer of real property from the seller to the buyer, and includes exchanges of real property between the seller and buyer, transactions for the creation of a real property sales contract within the meaning of Section 2985, and transactions for the creation of a leasehold exceeding one year&#x2019;s duration.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 18PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	(m)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&#x201C;Seller&#x201D; means the transferor in a real property transaction, and includes an owner who lists real property with an agent, whether or not a transfer results, or who receives an offer to purchase real property of which he or she is the owner from an agent on behalf of another.&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x201C;Seller&#x201D; includes both a vendor and a lessor.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 18PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	(n)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&#x201C;Selling agent&#x201D; means a listing agent who acts alone, or an agent who acts in cooperation with a listing agent, and who sells or finds and obtains a buyer for the real property, or an agent who locates property for a buyer or who finds a buyer for a property for which no listing exists and presents an offer in purchase to the seller.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 18PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	(o)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&#x201C;Subagent&#x201D; means a person to whom an agent delegates agency powers as provided in Article 5 (commencing with Section 2349) of Chapter 1 of Title 6.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, &#x201C;subagent&#x201D; does not include an associate licensee who is acting under the supervision of an agent in a real property transaction.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:6PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	2079.14.&nbsp;&nbsp;Listing agents and selling agents shall provide the seller and buyer in a real property transaction with a copy of the disclosure form specified in Section 2079.16, and, except as provided in subdivision (c), shall obtain a signed acknowledgment of receipt from that seller or buyer, except as provided in this section or Section 2079.15, as follows:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 18PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	The listing agent, if any, shall provide the disclosure form to the seller prior to entering into the listing agreement.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 18PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	The selling agent shall provide the disclosure form to the seller as soon as practicable prior to presenting the seller with an offer to purchase, unless the selling agent previously provided the seller with a copy of the disclosure form pursuant to subdivision.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 18PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	(c)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	Where the selling agent does not deal on a face-to-face basis with the seller, the disclosure form prepared by the selling agent may be furnished to the seller (and acknowledgment of receipt obtained for the selling agent from the seller) by the listing agent, or the selling agent may deliver the disclosure form by certified mail addressed to the seller at his or her last known address, in which case no signed acknowledgment of receipt is required.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 18PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	(d)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	The selling agent shall provide the disclosure form to the buyer as soon as practicable prior to execution of the buyer&#x2019;s offer to purchase, except that if the offer to purchase is not prepared by the selling agent, the selling agent shall present the disclosure form to the buyer not later than the next business day after the selling agent receives the offer to purchase from the buyer.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:6PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	2079.15.&nbsp;&nbsp;In any circumstance in which the seller or buyer refuses to sign an acknowledgment of receipt pursuant to Section 2079.14, the agent, or an associate licensee acting for an agent, shall set forth, sign, and date a written declaration of the facts of the refusal.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:6PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	2079 17.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 18PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	As soon as practicable, the selling agent shall disclose to the buyer and seller whether the selling agent is acting in the real property transaction exclusively as the buyer&#x2019;s agent, exclusively as the seller&#x2019;s agent, or as a dual agent representing both the buyer and the seller.&nbsp;&nbsp;This relationship shall be confirmed in the contract to purchase and sell real property or in a separate writing executed or acknowledged by the seller, the buyer, and the selling agent prior to or coincident with execution of that contract by the buyer and the seller, respectively.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 18PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	As soon as practicable, the listing agent shall disclose to the seller whether the listing agent is acting in the real property transaction exclusively as the seller&#x2019;s agent, or as a dual agent representing both the buyer and seller.&nbsp;&nbsp;This relationship shall be confirmed in the contract to purchase and sell real property or in a separate writing executed or acknowledged by the seller and the listing agent prior to or coincident with the execution of that contract by the seller.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 18PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	(c)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	The confirmation required by subdivisions (a) and (b) shall be in the following form:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT 18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 0PT 18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	_____is the Listing agent of (check one):&nbsp;&nbsp;( ) the seller exclusively; or ( ) both the buyer and seller.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT 18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	_____is the Selling agent,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	if not the same as the Listing Agent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	, of (check one): ( ) the buyer exclusively; or ( ) the seller exclusively; or ( ) both the buyer and seller.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT 0PT 6PT 18PT;TEXT-INDENT: -18PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	(d)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	The disclosures and confirmation required by this section shall be in addition to the disclosure required by Section 2079.14.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:6PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	2079.18.&nbsp;&nbsp;No selling agent in a reed property transaction may act as an agent for the buyer only, when the selling agent is also acting as the listing agent in the transaction.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:6PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	2079.19.&nbsp;&nbsp;The payment or compensation or the obligation to pay compensation to an agent by the seller or buyer is not necessarily determinative of a particular agency relationship between an agent end the seller or buyer.&nbsp;&nbsp;A listing agent and a selling agent may agree to share any compensation or commission paid, or any right in any compensation or commission for which an obligation arises as the result of a real estate transaction, and the terms of any such agreement shag not necessarily be determinative of a particular relationship.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:6PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	2079.20.&nbsp;&nbsp;Nothing in this article prevents an agent from selecting, as a condition of the agent&#x2019;s employment, a specific form of agency relationship not specifically prohibited by this article if the requirements of Section 2079.14 and Section 2079.17 are complied with.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:6PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	2079.21.&nbsp;&nbsp;A dual agent shall not disclose to the buyer that the seller is willing to sell the property at a price less than the listing price, without the express written consent of the seller.&nbsp;&nbsp;A dual agent shall not disclose to the seller that the buyer is willing to pay a price greater than the offering price, without the express written consent of the buyer.&nbsp;&nbsp;This section does not alter in any way the duty or responsibility of a dual agent to any principal with respect to confidential information other than price
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:6PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	2079.22.&nbsp;&nbsp;Nothing in this article precludes a listing agent from also being a selling agent, and the combination of these functions in one agent clues not, of itself, make that agent a duel agent.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:6PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	2079.23.&nbsp;&nbsp;A contract between the principal and agent may be modified or altered to change the agency relationship at any time before the performance of the act which is the object of the agency with the written consent of the parties to the agency relationship.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:6PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-JUSTIFY:INTER-IDEOGRAPH;BORDER-TOP:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:7PT;">
	2079.24.&nbsp;&nbsp;Nothing in this article shall be construed to either diminish the duty of disclosure owed buyers and sellers by agents and their associate licensees, subagents, and employees or to relieve agents and their associate licensees, subagents, and employees from liability for their conduct in connection with acts governed by this ankle or for any breach of a fiduciary duty or a duty of disclosure.
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:5.88235294117647%;MARGIN-RIGHT:5.88235294117647%;">
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:24PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 12PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	-
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	7
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;">
	&nbsp;-
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>

<EFX_CERTIFICATION>
<A NAME="FIS_CERTIFICATION"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	CERTIFICATION OF PRINCIPAL EXECUTIVE OFFICER
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	PURSUANT TO SECTION 302 OF THE SARBANES-OXLEY ACT OF 2002
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 9PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:9PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY:INLINE;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	I, Thomas W. Burns, certify that:
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:18PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:18PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 19.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9 ;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN,TIMES,SERIF;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:6PT 0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:6PT 0PT;FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;BORDER-BOTTOM:1PT NONE #D9D9D9;LINE-HEIGHT:100%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">
	1.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:3PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:3PT;WIDTH:3PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
